63// Resets the first pass file to the given position using a relative seek from
64// the current position.
65static void reset_fpf_position(TWO_PASS *p, const FIRSTPASS_STATS *position) {
66 p->stats_in = position;
67}
68
69// Read frame stats at an offset from the current position.
70static const FIRSTPASS_STATS *read_frame_stats(const TWO_PASS *p, int offset) {
71 if ((offset >= 0 && p->stats_in + offset >= p->stats_in_end) ||
72 (offset < 0 && p->stats_in + offset < p->stats_in_start)) {
73 return NULL;
74 }
75
76 return &p->stats_in[offset];
77}
78
79static int input_stats(TWO_PASS *p, FIRSTPASS_STATS *fps) {
80 if (p->stats_in >= p->stats_in_end) return EOF;
81
82 *fps = *p->stats_in;
83 ++p->stats_in;
84 return 1;
85}

213// Calculate an active area of the image that discounts formatting
214// bars and partially discounts other 0 energy areas.
215#define MIN_ACTIVE_AREA 0.5
216#define MAX_ACTIVE_AREA 1.0
217static double calculate_active_area(const FRAME_INFO *frame_info,
218 const FIRSTPASS_STATS *this_frame) {
219 double active_pct;
220
221 active_pct =
222 1.0 -
223 ((this_frame->intra_skip_pct / 2) +
224 ((this_frame->inactive_zone_rows * 2) / (double)frame_info->mb_rows));
225 return fclamp(active_pct, MIN_ACTIVE_AREA, MAX_ACTIVE_AREA);
226}
227
228// Get the average weighted error for the clip (or corpus)
229static double get_distribution_av_err(VP9_COMP *cpi, TWO_PASS *const twopass) {
230 const double av_weight =
231 twopass->total_stats.weight / twopass->total_stats.count;
232
233 if (cpi->oxcf.vbr_corpus_complexity)
234 return av_weight * twopass->mean_mod_score;
235 else
236 return (twopass->total_stats.coded_error * av_weight) /
237 twopass->total_stats.count;
238}
239
240#define ACT_AREA_CORRECTION 0.5
241// Calculate a modified Error used in distributing bits between easier and
242// harder frames.
243static double calculate_mod_frame_score(const VP9_COMP *cpi,
244 const VP9EncoderConfig *oxcf,
245 const FIRSTPASS_STATS *this_frame,
246 const double av_err) {
247 double modified_score =
248 av_err * pow(this_frame->coded_error * this_frame->weight /
249 DOUBLE_DIVIDE_CHECK(av_err),
250 oxcf->two_pass_vbrbias / 100.0);
251
252 // Correction for active area. Frames with a reduced active area
253 // (eg due to formatting bars) have a higher error per mb for the
254 // remaining active MBs. The correction here assumes that coding
255 // 0.5N blocks of complexity 2X is a little easier than coding N
256 // blocks of complexity X.
257 modified_score *= pow(calculate_active_area(&cpi->frame_info, this_frame),
258 ACT_AREA_CORRECTION);
259
260 return modified_score;
261}
262
263static double calc_norm_frame_score(const VP9EncoderConfig *oxcf,
264 const FRAME_INFO *frame_info,
265 const FIRSTPASS_STATS *this_frame,
266 double mean_mod_score, double av_err) {
267 double modified_score =
268 av_err * pow(this_frame->coded_error * this_frame->weight /
269 DOUBLE_DIVIDE_CHECK(av_err),
270 oxcf->two_pass_vbrbias / 100.0);
271
272 const double min_score = (double)(oxcf->two_pass_vbrmin_section) / 100.0;
273 const double max_score = (double)(oxcf->two_pass_vbrmax_section) / 100.0;
274
275 // Correction for active area. Frames with a reduced active area
276 // (eg due to formatting bars) have a higher error per mb for the
277 // remaining active MBs. The correction here assumes that coding
278 // 0.5N blocks of complexity 2X is a little easier than coding N
279 // blocks of complexity X.
280 modified_score *=
281 pow(calculate_active_area(frame_info, this_frame), ACT_AREA_CORRECTION);
282
283 // Normalize to a midpoint score.
284 modified_score /= DOUBLE_DIVIDE_CHECK(mean_mod_score);
285 return fclamp(modified_score, min_score, max_score);
286}
287
288static double calculate_norm_frame_score(const VP9_COMP *cpi,
289 const TWO_PASS *twopass,
290 const VP9EncoderConfig *oxcf,
291 const FIRSTPASS_STATS *this_frame,
292 const double av_err) {
293 return calc_norm_frame_score(oxcf, &cpi->frame_info, this_frame,
294 twopass->mean_mod_score, av_err);
295}

297// This function returns the maximum target rate per frame.
298static int frame_max_bits(const RATE_CONTROL *rc,
299 const VP9EncoderConfig *oxcf) {
300 int64_t max_bits = ((int64_t)rc->avg_frame_bandwidth *
301 (int64_t)oxcf->two_pass_vbrmax_section) /
302 100;
303 if (max_bits < 0)
304 max_bits = 0;
305 else if (max_bits > rc->max_frame_bandwidth)
306 max_bits = rc->max_frame_bandwidth;
307
308 return (int)max_bits;
309}

312 zero_stats(&cpi->twopass.total_stats);

315void vp9_end_first_pass(VP9_COMP *cpi) {
316 output_stats(&cpi->twopass.total_stats);

318 vpx_free(cpi->twopass.fp_mb_float_stats);
319 cpi->twopass.fp_mb_float_stats = NULL;
320}

322static vpx_variance_fn_t get_block_variance_fn(BLOCK_SIZE bsize) {
323 switch (bsize) {
324 case BLOCK_8X8: return vpx_mse8x8;
325 case BLOCK_16X8: return vpx_mse16x8;
326 case BLOCK_8X16: return vpx_mse8x16;
327 default: return vpx_mse16x16;
328 }
329}
330
331static unsigned int get_prediction_error(BLOCK_SIZE bsize,
332 const struct buf_2d *src,
333 const struct buf_2d *ref) {
334 unsigned int sse;
335 const vpx_variance_fn_t fn = get_block_variance_fn(bsize);
336 fn(src->buf, src->stride, ref->buf, ref->stride, &sse);
337 return sse;
338}

340#if CONFIG_VP9_HIGHBITDEPTH
341static vpx_variance_fn_t highbd_get_block_variance_fn(BLOCK_SIZE bsize,
342 int bd) {
343 switch (bd) {
344 default:
345 switch (bsize) {
346 case BLOCK_8X8: return vpx_highbd_8_mse8x8;

350 }

354 case BLOCK_8X8: return vpx_highbd_10_mse8x8;

356 case BLOCK_8X16: return vpx_highbd_10_mse8x16;
357 default: return vpx_highbd_10_mse16x16;
358 }
359 break;
360 case 12:
361 switch (bsize) {
362 case BLOCK_8X8: return vpx_highbd_12_mse8x8;
363 case BLOCK_16X8: return vpx_highbd_12_mse16x8;
364 case BLOCK_8X16: return vpx_highbd_12_mse8x16;
365 default: return vpx_highbd_12_mse16x16;
366 }
367 break;
368 }
369}

382// Refine the motion search range according to the frame dimension
383// for first pass test.
384static int get_search_range(const VP9_COMP *cpi) {
385 int sr = 0;
386 const int dim = VPXMIN(cpi->initial_width, cpi->initial_height);
387
388 while ((dim << sr) < MAX_FULL_PEL_VAL) ++sr;
389 return sr;
390}
391
392// Reduce limits to keep the motion search within MV_MAX of ref_mv. Not doing
393// this can be problematic for big videos (8K) and may cause assert failure
394// (or memory violation) in mv_cost. Limits are only modified if they would
395// be non-empty. Returns 1 if limits are non-empty.
396static int intersect_limits_with_mv_max(MvLimits *mv_limits, const MV *ref_mv) {
397 const int row_min =
398 VPXMAX(mv_limits->row_min, (ref_mv->row + 7 - MV_MAX) >> 3);
399 const int row_max =
400 VPXMIN(mv_limits->row_max, (ref_mv->row - 1 + MV_MAX) >> 3);
401 const int col_min =
402 VPXMAX(mv_limits->col_min, (ref_mv->col + 7 - MV_MAX) >> 3);
403 const int col_max =
404 VPXMIN(mv_limits->col_max, (ref_mv->col - 1 + MV_MAX) >> 3);
405 if (row_min > row_max || col_min > col_max) {
406 return 0;
407 }
408 mv_limits->row_min = row_min;
409 mv_limits->row_max = row_max;
410 mv_limits->col_min = col_min;
411 mv_limits->col_max = col_max;
412 return 1;
413}

415static void first_pass_motion_search(VP9_COMP *cpi, MACROBLOCK *x,
416 const MV *ref_mv, MV *best_mv,
417 int *best_motion_err) {
418 MACROBLOCKD *const xd = &x->e_mbd;
419 MV tmp_mv = { 0, 0 };
420 MV ref_mv_full = { ref_mv->row >> 3, ref_mv->col >> 3 };
421 int num00, tmp_err, n;
422 const BLOCK_SIZE bsize = xd->mi[0]->sb_type;
423 vp9_variance_fn_ptr_t v_fn_ptr = cpi->fn_ptr[bsize];
424 const int new_mv_mode_penalty = NEW_MV_MODE_PENALTY;
425
426 int step_param = 3;
427 int further_steps = (MAX_MVSEARCH_STEPS - 1) - step_param;
428 const int sr = get_search_range(cpi);
429 const MvLimits tmp_mv_limits = x->mv_limits;
430 step_param += sr;
431 further_steps -= sr;
432
433 if (!intersect_limits_with_mv_max(&x->mv_limits, ref_mv)) {
434 return;
435 }
436
437 // Override the default variance function to use MSE.
438 v_fn_ptr.vf = get_block_variance_fn(bsize);
439#if CONFIG_VP9_HIGHBITDEPTH
440 if (xd->cur_buf->flags & YV12_FLAG_HIGHBITDEPTH) {
441 v_fn_ptr.vf = highbd_get_block_variance_fn(bsize, xd->bd);
442 }
443#endif // CONFIG_VP9_HIGHBITDEPTH
444
445 // Center the initial step/diamond search on best mv.
446 tmp_err = cpi->diamond_search_sad(x, &cpi->ss_cfg, &ref_mv_full, &tmp_mv,
447 step_param, x->sadperbit16, &num00,
448 &v_fn_ptr, ref_mv);
449 if (tmp_err < INT_MAX)
450 tmp_err = vp9_get_mvpred_var(x, &tmp_mv, ref_mv, &v_fn_ptr, 1);
451 if (tmp_err < INT_MAX - new_mv_mode_penalty) tmp_err += new_mv_mode_penalty;
452
453 if (tmp_err < *best_motion_err) {
454 *best_motion_err = tmp_err;
455 *best_mv = tmp_mv;
456 }
457
458 // Carry out further step/diamond searches as necessary.
459 n = num00;
460 num00 = 0;
461
462 while (n < further_steps) {
463 ++n;
464
465 if (num00) {
466 --num00;
467 } else {
468 tmp_err = cpi->diamond_search_sad(x, &cpi->ss_cfg, &ref_mv_full, &tmp_mv,
469 step_param + n, x->sadperbit16, &num00,
470 &v_fn_ptr, ref_mv);
471 if (tmp_err < INT_MAX)
472 tmp_err = vp9_get_mvpred_var(x, &tmp_mv, ref_mv, &v_fn_ptr, 1);
473 if (tmp_err < INT_MAX - new_mv_mode_penalty)
474 tmp_err += new_mv_mode_penalty;
475
476 if (tmp_err < *best_motion_err) {
477 *best_motion_err = tmp_err;
478 *best_mv = tmp_mv;
479 }
480 }
481 }
482 x->mv_limits = tmp_mv_limits;
483}

485static BLOCK_SIZE get_bsize(const VP9_COMMON *cm, int mb_row, int mb_col) {
486 if (2 * mb_col + 1 < cm->mi_cols) {
487 return 2 * mb_row + 1 < cm->mi_rows ? BLOCK_16X16 : BLOCK_16X8;
488 } else {
489 return 2 * mb_row + 1 < cm->mi_rows ? BLOCK_8X16 : BLOCK_8X8;
490 }
491}

493static int find_fp_qindex(vpx_bit_depth_t bit_depth) {
494 int i;
495
496 for (i = 0; i < QINDEX_RANGE; ++i)
497 if (vp9_convert_qindex_to_q(i, bit_depth) >= FIRST_PASS_Q) break;
498
499 if (i == QINDEX_RANGE) i--;
500
501 return i;
502}

504static void set_first_pass_params(VP9_COMP *cpi) {
505 VP9_COMMON *const cm = &cpi->common;
506 if (!cpi->refresh_alt_ref_frame &&
507 (cm->current_video_frame == 0 || (cpi->frame_flags & FRAMEFLAGS_KEY))) {
508 cm->frame_type = KEY_FRAME;
509 } else {
510 cm->frame_type = INTER_FRAME;
511 }
512 // Do not use periodic key frames.
513 cpi->rc.frames_to_key = INT_MAX;
514}

516// Scale an sse threshold to account for 8/10/12 bit.
517static int scale_sse_threshold(VP9_COMMON *cm, int thresh) {
518 int ret_val = thresh;
519#if CONFIG_VP9_HIGHBITDEPTH
520 if (cm->use_highbitdepth) {
521 switch (cm->bit_depth) {
522 case VPX_BITS_8: ret_val = thresh; break;
523 case VPX_BITS_10: ret_val = thresh << 4; break;
524 default:
525 assert(cm->bit_depth == VPX_BITS_12);
526 ret_val = thresh << 8;
527 break;
528 }
529 }
530#else
531 (void)cm;
532#endif // CONFIG_VP9_HIGHBITDEPTH
533 return ret_val;
534}
535
536// This threshold is used to track blocks where to all intents and purposes
537// the intra prediction error 0. Though the metric we test against
538// is technically a sse we are mainly interested in blocks where all the pixels
539// in the 8 bit domain have an error of <= 1 (where error = sse) so a
540// linear scaling for 10 and 12 bit gives similar results.
541#define UL_INTRA_THRESH 50
542static int get_ul_intra_threshold(VP9_COMMON *cm) {
543 int ret_val = UL_INTRA_THRESH;
544#if CONFIG_VP9_HIGHBITDEPTH
545 if (cm->use_highbitdepth) {
546 switch (cm->bit_depth) {
547 case VPX_BITS_8: ret_val = UL_INTRA_THRESH; break;
548 case VPX_BITS_10: ret_val = UL_INTRA_THRESH << 2; break;
549 default:
550 assert(cm->bit_depth == VPX_BITS_12);
551 ret_val = UL_INTRA_THRESH << 4;
552 break;
553 }
554 }
555#else
556 (void)cm;
557#endif // CONFIG_VP9_HIGHBITDEPTH
558 return ret_val;
559}
560
561#define SMOOTH_INTRA_THRESH 4000
562static int get_smooth_intra_threshold(VP9_COMMON *cm) {
563 int ret_val = SMOOTH_INTRA_THRESH;
564#if CONFIG_VP9_HIGHBITDEPTH
565 if (cm->use_highbitdepth) {
566 switch (cm->bit_depth) {
567 case VPX_BITS_8: ret_val = SMOOTH_INTRA_THRESH; break;
568 case VPX_BITS_10: ret_val = SMOOTH_INTRA_THRESH << 4; break;
569 default:
570 assert(cm->bit_depth == VPX_BITS_12);
571 ret_val = SMOOTH_INTRA_THRESH << 8;
572 break;
573 }
574 }
575#else
576 (void)cm;
577#endif // CONFIG_VP9_HIGHBITDEPTH
578 return ret_val;
579}
580
581#define FP_DN_THRESH 8
582#define FP_MAX_DN_THRESH 24
583#define KERNEL_SIZE 3
584
585// Baseline Kernal weights for first pass noise metric
586static uint8_t fp_dn_kernal_3[KERNEL_SIZE * KERNEL_SIZE] = { 1, 2, 1, 2, 4,
587 2, 1, 2, 1 };
588
589// Estimate noise at a single point based on the impace of a spatial kernal
590// on the point value
591static int fp_estimate_point_noise(uint8_t *src_ptr, const int stride) {
592 int sum_weight = 0;
593 int sum_val = 0;
594 int i, j;
595 int max_diff = 0;
596 int diff;
597 int dn_diff;
598 uint8_t *tmp_ptr;
599 uint8_t *kernal_ptr;
600 uint8_t dn_val;
601 uint8_t centre_val = *src_ptr;
602
603 kernal_ptr = fp_dn_kernal_3;
604
605 // Apply the kernal
606 tmp_ptr = src_ptr - stride - 1;
607 for (i = 0; i < KERNEL_SIZE; ++i) {
608 for (j = 0; j < KERNEL_SIZE; ++j) {
609 diff = abs((int)centre_val - (int)tmp_ptr[j]);
610 max_diff = VPXMAX(max_diff, diff);
611 if (diff <= FP_DN_THRESH) {
612 sum_weight += *kernal_ptr;
613 sum_val += (int)tmp_ptr[j] * (int)*kernal_ptr;
614 }
615 ++kernal_ptr;
616 }
617 tmp_ptr += stride;
618 }
619
620 if (max_diff < FP_MAX_DN_THRESH)
621 // Update the source value with the new filtered value
622 dn_val = (sum_val + (sum_weight >> 1)) / sum_weight;
623 else
624 dn_val = *src_ptr;
625
626 // return the noise energy as the square of the difference between the
627 // denoised and raw value.
628 dn_diff = (int)*src_ptr - (int)dn_val;
629 return dn_diff * dn_diff;
630}
631#if CONFIG_VP9_HIGHBITDEPTH
632static int fp_highbd_estimate_point_noise(uint8_t *src_ptr, const int stride) {
633 int sum_weight = 0;
634 int sum_val = 0;
635 int i, j;
636 int max_diff = 0;
637 int diff;
638 int dn_diff;
639 uint8_t *tmp_ptr;
640 uint16_t *tmp_ptr16;
641 uint8_t *kernal_ptr;
642 uint16_t dn_val;
643 uint16_t centre_val = *CONVERT_TO_SHORTPTR(src_ptr);
644
645 kernal_ptr = fp_dn_kernal_3;
646
647 // Apply the kernal
648 tmp_ptr = src_ptr - stride - 1;
649 for (i = 0; i < KERNEL_SIZE; ++i) {
650 tmp_ptr16 = CONVERT_TO_SHORTPTR(tmp_ptr);
651 for (j = 0; j < KERNEL_SIZE; ++j) {
652 diff = abs((int)centre_val - (int)tmp_ptr16[j]);
653 max_diff = VPXMAX(max_diff, diff);
654 if (diff <= FP_DN_THRESH) {
655 sum_weight += *kernal_ptr;
656 sum_val += (int)tmp_ptr16[j] * (int)*kernal_ptr;
657 }
658 ++kernal_ptr;
659 }
660 tmp_ptr += stride;
661 }
662
663 if (max_diff < FP_MAX_DN_THRESH)
664 // Update the source value with the new filtered value
665 dn_val = (sum_val + (sum_weight >> 1)) / sum_weight;
666 else
667 dn_val = *CONVERT_TO_SHORTPTR(src_ptr);
668
669 // return the noise energy as the square of the difference between the
670 // denoised and raw value.
671 dn_diff = (int)(*CONVERT_TO_SHORTPTR(src_ptr)) - (int)dn_val;
672 return dn_diff * dn_diff;
673}
674#endif
675
676// Estimate noise for a block.
677static int fp_estimate_block_noise(MACROBLOCK *x, BLOCK_SIZE bsize) {
678#if CONFIG_VP9_HIGHBITDEPTH
679 MACROBLOCKD *xd = &x->e_mbd;
680#endif
681 uint8_t *src_ptr = &x->plane[0].src.buf[0];
682 const int width = num_4x4_blocks_wide_lookup[bsize] * 4;
683 const int height = num_4x4_blocks_high_lookup[bsize] * 4;
684 int w, h;
685 int stride = x->plane[0].src.stride;
686 int block_noise = 0;
687
688 // Sampled points to reduce cost overhead.
689 for (h = 0; h < height; h += 2) {
690 for (w = 0; w < width; w += 2) {
691#if CONFIG_VP9_HIGHBITDEPTH
692 if (xd->cur_buf->flags & YV12_FLAG_HIGHBITDEPTH)
693 block_noise += fp_highbd_estimate_point_noise(src_ptr, stride);
694 else
695 block_noise += fp_estimate_point_noise(src_ptr, stride);
696#else
697 block_noise += fp_estimate_point_noise(src_ptr, stride);
698#endif
699 ++src_ptr;
700 }
701 src_ptr += (stride - width);
702 }
703 return block_noise << 2; // Scale << 2 to account for sampling.
704}

706// This function is called to test the functionality of row based
707// multi-threading in unit tests for bit-exactness
708static void accumulate_floating_point_stats(VP9_COMP *cpi,
709 TileDataEnc *first_tile_col) {

724 }
725 }

728static void first_pass_stat_calc(VP9_COMP *cpi, FIRSTPASS_STATS *fps,
729 FIRSTPASS_DATA *fp_acc_data) {
730 VP9_COMMON *const cm = &cpi->common;
731 // The minimum error here insures some bit allocation to frames even
732 // in static regions. The allocation per MB declines for larger formats
733 // where the typical "real" energy per MB also falls.
734 // Initial estimate here uses sqrt(mbs) to define the min_err, where the
735 // number of mbs is proportional to the image area.
736 const int num_mbs = (cpi->oxcf.resize_mode != RESIZE_NONE) ? cpi->initial_mbs
737 : cpi->common.MBs;
738 const double min_err = 200 * sqrt(num_mbs);
739
740 // Clamp the image start to rows/2. This number of rows is discarded top
741 // and bottom as dead data so rows / 2 means the frame is blank.
742 if ((fp_acc_data->image_data_start_row > cm->mb_rows / 2) ||
743 (fp_acc_data->image_data_start_row == INVALID_ROW)) {
744 fp_acc_data->image_data_start_row = cm->mb_rows / 2;
745 }
746 // Exclude any image dead zone
747 if (fp_acc_data->image_data_start_row > 0) {
748 fp_acc_data->intra_skip_count =
749 VPXMAX(0, fp_acc_data->intra_skip_count -
750 (fp_acc_data->image_data_start_row * cm->mb_cols * 2));
751 }
752
753 fp_acc_data->intra_factor = fp_acc_data->intra_factor / (double)num_mbs;
754 fp_acc_data->brightness_factor =
755 fp_acc_data->brightness_factor / (double)num_mbs;
756 fps->weight = fp_acc_data->intra_factor * fp_acc_data->brightness_factor;
757
758 fps->frame = cm->current_video_frame;
759 fps->spatial_layer_id = cpi->svc.spatial_layer_id;
760
761 fps->coded_error =
762 ((double)(fp_acc_data->coded_error >> 8) + min_err) / num_mbs;
763 fps->sr_coded_error =
764 ((double)(fp_acc_data->sr_coded_error >> 8) + min_err) / num_mbs;
765 fps->intra_error =
766 ((double)(fp_acc_data->intra_error >> 8) + min_err) / num_mbs;
767
768 fps->frame_noise_energy =
769 (double)(fp_acc_data->frame_noise_energy) / (double)num_mbs;
770 fps->count = 1.0;
771 fps->pcnt_inter = (double)(fp_acc_data->intercount) / num_mbs;
772 fps->pcnt_second_ref = (double)(fp_acc_data->second_ref_count) / num_mbs;
773 fps->pcnt_neutral = (double)(fp_acc_data->neutral_count) / num_mbs;
774 fps->pcnt_intra_low = (double)(fp_acc_data->intra_count_low) / num_mbs;
775 fps->pcnt_intra_high = (double)(fp_acc_data->intra_count_high) / num_mbs;
776 fps->intra_skip_pct = (double)(fp_acc_data->intra_skip_count) / num_mbs;
777 fps->intra_smooth_pct = (double)(fp_acc_data->intra_smooth_count) / num_mbs;
778 fps->inactive_zone_rows = (double)(fp_acc_data->image_data_start_row);
779 // Currently set to 0 as most issues relate to letter boxing.
780 fps->inactive_zone_cols = (double)0;
781
782 if (fp_acc_data->mvcount > 0) {
783 fps->MVr = (double)(fp_acc_data->sum_mvr) / fp_acc_data->mvcount;
784 fps->mvr_abs = (double)(fp_acc_data->sum_mvr_abs) / fp_acc_data->mvcount;
785 fps->MVc = (double)(fp_acc_data->sum_mvc) / fp_acc_data->mvcount;
786 fps->mvc_abs = (double)(fp_acc_data->sum_mvc_abs) / fp_acc_data->mvcount;
787 fps->MVrv = ((double)(fp_acc_data->sum_mvrs) -
788 ((double)(fp_acc_data->sum_mvr) * (fp_acc_data->sum_mvr) /
789 fp_acc_data->mvcount)) /
790 fp_acc_data->mvcount;
791 fps->MVcv = ((double)(fp_acc_data->sum_mvcs) -
792 ((double)(fp_acc_data->sum_mvc) * (fp_acc_data->sum_mvc) /
793 fp_acc_data->mvcount)) /
794 fp_acc_data->mvcount;
795 fps->mv_in_out_count =
796 (double)(fp_acc_data->sum_in_vectors) / (fp_acc_data->mvcount * 2);
797 fps->pcnt_motion = (double)(fp_acc_data->mvcount) / num_mbs;
798 } else {
799 fps->MVr = 0.0;
800 fps->mvr_abs = 0.0;
801 fps->MVc = 0.0;
802 fps->mvc_abs = 0.0;
803 fps->MVrv = 0.0;
804 fps->MVcv = 0.0;
805 fps->mv_in_out_count = 0.0;
806 fps->pcnt_motion = 0.0;
807 }
808}

838 : VPXMIN(this_tile->fp_data.image_data_start_row,
839 fp_acc_data->image_data_start_row);
840}

858#define NZ_MOTION_PENALTY 128
859#define INTRA_MODE_PENALTY 1024
860void vp9_first_pass_encode_tile_mb_row(VP9_COMP *cpi, ThreadData *td,
861 FIRSTPASS_DATA *fp_acc_data,
862 TileDataEnc *tile_data, MV *best_ref_mv,
863 int mb_row) {
864 int mb_col;
865 MACROBLOCK *const x = &td->mb;
866 VP9_COMMON *const cm = &cpi->common;
867 MACROBLOCKD *const xd = &x->e_mbd;
868 TileInfo tile = tile_data->tile_info;
869 const int mb_col_start = ROUND_POWER_OF_TWO(tile.mi_col_start, 1);
870 const int mb_col_end = ROUND_POWER_OF_TWO(tile.mi_col_end, 1);
871 struct macroblock_plane *const p = x->plane;
872 struct macroblockd_plane *const pd = xd->plane;
873 const PICK_MODE_CONTEXT *ctx = &td->pc_root->none;
874 int i, c;
875 int num_mb_cols = get_num_cols(tile_data->tile_info, 1);
876
877 int recon_yoffset, recon_uvoffset;
878 const int intrapenalty = INTRA_MODE_PENALTY;
879 const MV zero_mv = { 0, 0 };
880 int recon_y_stride, recon_uv_stride, uv_mb_height;
881
882 YV12_BUFFER_CONFIG *const lst_yv12 = get_ref_frame_buffer(cpi, LAST_FRAME);
883 YV12_BUFFER_CONFIG *gld_yv12 = get_ref_frame_buffer(cpi, GOLDEN_FRAME);
884 YV12_BUFFER_CONFIG *const new_yv12 = get_frame_new_buffer(cm);
885 const YV12_BUFFER_CONFIG *first_ref_buf = lst_yv12;
886
887 MODE_INFO mi_above, mi_left;
888
889 double mb_intra_factor;
890 double mb_brightness_factor;
891 double mb_neutral_count;
892 int scaled_low_intra_thresh = scale_sse_threshold(cm, LOW_I_THRESH);
893
894 // First pass code requires valid last and new frame buffers.
895 assert(new_yv12 != NULL);
896 assert(frame_is_intra_only(cm) || (lst_yv12 != NULL));
897
898 xd->mi = cm->mi_grid_visible + xd->mi_stride * (mb_row << 1) + mb_col_start;
899 xd->mi[0] = cm->mi + xd->mi_stride * (mb_row << 1) + mb_col_start;
900
901 for (i = 0; i < MAX_MB_PLANE; ++i) {
902 p[i].coeff = ctx->coeff_pbuf[i][1];
903 p[i].qcoeff = ctx->qcoeff_pbuf[i][1];
904 pd[i].dqcoeff = ctx->dqcoeff_pbuf[i][1];
905 p[i].eobs = ctx->eobs_pbuf[i][1];
906 }
907
908 recon_y_stride = new_yv12->y_stride;
909 recon_uv_stride = new_yv12->uv_stride;
910 uv_mb_height = 16 >> (new_yv12->y_height > new_yv12->uv_height);
911
912 // Reset above block coeffs.
913 recon_yoffset = (mb_row * recon_y_stride * 16) + mb_col_start * 16;
914 recon_uvoffset =
915 (mb_row * recon_uv_stride * uv_mb_height) + mb_col_start * uv_mb_height;
916
917 // Set up limit values for motion vectors to prevent them extending
918 // outside the UMV borders.
919 x->mv_limits.row_min = -((mb_row * 16) + BORDER_MV_PIXELS_B16);
920 x->mv_limits.row_max =
921 ((cm->mb_rows - 1 - mb_row) * 16) + BORDER_MV_PIXELS_B16;
922
923 for (mb_col = mb_col_start, c = 0; mb_col < mb_col_end; ++mb_col, c++) {
924 int this_error;
925 int this_intra_error;
926 const int use_dc_pred = (mb_col || mb_row) && (!mb_col || !mb_row);
927 const BLOCK_SIZE bsize = get_bsize(cm, mb_row, mb_col);
928 double log_intra;
929 int level_sample;
930 const int mb_index = mb_row * cm->mb_cols + mb_col;
931
932#if CONFIG_FP_MB_STATS
933 const int mb_index = mb_row * cm->mb_cols + mb_col;
934#endif
935
936 (*(cpi->row_mt_sync_read_ptr))(&tile_data->row_mt_sync, mb_row, c);
937
938 // Adjust to the next column of MBs.
939 x->plane[0].src.buf = cpi->Source->y_buffer +
940 mb_row * 16 * x->plane[0].src.stride + mb_col * 16;
941 x->plane[1].src.buf = cpi->Source->u_buffer +
942 mb_row * uv_mb_height * x->plane[1].src.stride +
943 mb_col * uv_mb_height;
944 x->plane[2].src.buf = cpi->Source->v_buffer +
945 mb_row * uv_mb_height * x->plane[1].src.stride +
946 mb_col * uv_mb_height;
947
948 vpx_clear_system_state();
949
950 xd->plane[0].dst.buf = new_yv12->y_buffer + recon_yoffset;
951 xd->plane[1].dst.buf = new_yv12->u_buffer + recon_uvoffset;
952 xd->plane[2].dst.buf = new_yv12->v_buffer + recon_uvoffset;
953 xd->mi[0]->sb_type = bsize;
954 xd->mi[0]->ref_frame[0] = INTRA_FRAME;
955 set_mi_row_col(xd, &tile, mb_row << 1, num_8x8_blocks_high_lookup[bsize],
956 mb_col << 1, num_8x8_blocks_wide_lookup[bsize], cm->mi_rows,
957 cm->mi_cols);
958 // Are edges available for intra prediction?
959 // Since the firstpass does not populate the mi_grid_visible,
960 // above_mi/left_mi must be overwritten with a nonzero value when edges
961 // are available. Required by vp9_predict_intra_block().
962 xd->above_mi = (mb_row != 0) ? &mi_above : NULL;
963 xd->left_mi = ((mb_col << 1) > tile.mi_col_start) ? &mi_left : NULL;
964
965 // Do intra 16x16 prediction.
966 x->skip_encode = 0;
967 x->fp_src_pred = 0;
968 // Do intra prediction based on source pixels for tile boundaries
969 if (mb_col == mb_col_start && mb_col != 0) {
970 xd->left_mi = &mi_left;
971 x->fp_src_pred = 1;
972 }
973 xd->mi[0]->mode = DC_PRED;
974 xd->mi[0]->tx_size =
975 use_dc_pred ? (bsize >= BLOCK_16X16 ? TX_16X16 : TX_8X8) : TX_4X4;
976 // Fix - zero the 16x16 block first. This ensures correct this_error for
977 // block sizes smaller than 16x16.
978 vp9_zero_array(x->plane[0].src_diff, 256);
979 vp9_encode_intra_block_plane(x, bsize, 0, 0);
980 this_error = vpx_get_mb_ss(x->plane[0].src_diff);
981 this_intra_error = this_error;
982
983 // Keep a record of blocks that have very low intra error residual
984 // (i.e. are in effect completely flat and untextured in the intra
985 // domain). In natural videos this is uncommon, but it is much more
986 // common in animations, graphics and screen content, so may be used
987 // as a signal to detect these types of content.
988 if (this_error < get_ul_intra_threshold(cm)) {
989 ++(fp_acc_data->intra_skip_count);
990 } else if ((mb_col > 0) &&
991 (fp_acc_data->image_data_start_row == INVALID_ROW)) {
992 fp_acc_data->image_data_start_row = mb_row;
993 }
994
995 // Blocks that are mainly smooth in the intra domain.
996 // Some special accounting for CQ but also these are better for testing
997 // noise levels.
998 if (this_error < get_smooth_intra_threshold(cm)) {
999 ++(fp_acc_data->intra_smooth_count);
1000 }
1001
1002 // Special case noise measurement for first frame.
1003 if (cm->current_video_frame == 0) {
1004 if (this_intra_error < scale_sse_threshold(cm, LOW_I_THRESH)) {
1005 fp_acc_data->frame_noise_energy += fp_estimate_block_noise(x, bsize);
1006 } else {
1007 fp_acc_data->frame_noise_energy += (int64_t)SECTION_NOISE_DEF;
1008 }
1009 }
1010
1011#if CONFIG_VP9_HIGHBITDEPTH
1012 if (cm->use_highbitdepth) {
1013 switch (cm->bit_depth) {
1014 case VPX_BITS_8: break;
1015 case VPX_BITS_10: this_error >>= 4; break;
1016 default:
1017 assert(cm->bit_depth == VPX_BITS_12);
1018 this_error >>= 8;
1019 break;
1020 }
1021 }
1022#endif // CONFIG_VP9_HIGHBITDEPTH
1023
1024 vpx_clear_system_state();
1025 log_intra = log(this_error + 1.0);
1026 if (log_intra < 10.0) {
1027 mb_intra_factor = 1.0 + ((10.0 - log_intra) * 0.05);
1028 fp_acc_data->intra_factor += mb_intra_factor;
1029 if (cpi->row_mt_bit_exact)
1030 cpi->twopass.fp_mb_float_stats[mb_index].frame_mb_intra_factor =
1031 mb_intra_factor;
1032 } else {
1033 fp_acc_data->intra_factor += 1.0;
1034 if (cpi->row_mt_bit_exact)
1035 cpi->twopass.fp_mb_float_stats[mb_index].frame_mb_intra_factor = 1.0;
1036 }
1037
1038#if CONFIG_VP9_HIGHBITDEPTH
1039 if (cm->use_highbitdepth)
1040 level_sample = CONVERT_TO_SHORTPTR(x->plane[0].src.buf)[0];
1041 else
1042 level_sample = x->plane[0].src.buf[0];
1043#else
1044 level_sample = x->plane[0].src.buf[0];
1045#endif
1046 if ((level_sample < DARK_THRESH) && (log_intra < 9.0)) {
1047 mb_brightness_factor = 1.0 + (0.01 * (DARK_THRESH - level_sample));
1048 fp_acc_data->brightness_factor += mb_brightness_factor;
1049 if (cpi->row_mt_bit_exact)
1050 cpi->twopass.fp_mb_float_stats[mb_index].frame_mb_brightness_factor =
1051 mb_brightness_factor;
1052 } else {
1053 fp_acc_data->brightness_factor += 1.0;
1054 if (cpi->row_mt_bit_exact)
1055 cpi->twopass.fp_mb_float_stats[mb_index].frame_mb_brightness_factor =
1056 1.0;
1057 }
1058
1059 // Intrapenalty below deals with situations where the intra and inter
1060 // error scores are very low (e.g. a plain black frame).
1061 // We do not have special cases in first pass for 0,0 and nearest etc so
1062 // all inter modes carry an overhead cost estimate for the mv.
1063 // When the error score is very low this causes us to pick all or lots of
1064 // INTRA modes and throw lots of key frames.
1065 // This penalty adds a cost matching that of a 0,0 mv to the intra case.
1066 this_error += intrapenalty;
1067
1068 // Accumulate the intra error.
1069 fp_acc_data->intra_error += (int64_t)this_error;
1070
1071#if CONFIG_FP_MB_STATS
1072 if (cpi->use_fp_mb_stats) {
1073 // initialization
1074 cpi->twopass.frame_mb_stats_buf[mb_index] = 0;
1075 }
1076#endif
1077
1078 // Set up limit values for motion vectors to prevent them extending
1079 // outside the UMV borders.
1080 x->mv_limits.col_min = -((mb_col * 16) + BORDER_MV_PIXELS_B16);
1081 x->mv_limits.col_max =
1082 ((cm->mb_cols - 1 - mb_col) * 16) + BORDER_MV_PIXELS_B16;
1083
1084 // Other than for intra-only frame do a motion search.
1085 if (!frame_is_intra_only(cm)) {
1086 int tmp_err, motion_error, this_motion_error, raw_motion_error;
1087 // Assume 0,0 motion with no mv overhead.
1088 MV mv = { 0, 0 }, tmp_mv = { 0, 0 };
1089 struct buf_2d unscaled_last_source_buf_2d;
1090 vp9_variance_fn_ptr_t v_fn_ptr = cpi->fn_ptr[bsize];
1091
1092#if CONFIG_RATE_CTRL
1093 // Store zero mv as default
1094 store_fp_motion_vector(cpi, &mv, mb_row, mb_col, LAST_FRAME, 0);
1095#endif // CONFIG_RAGE_CTRL
1096
1097 xd->plane[0].pre[0].buf = first_ref_buf->y_buffer + recon_yoffset;
1098#if CONFIG_VP9_HIGHBITDEPTH
1099 if (xd->cur_buf->flags & YV12_FLAG_HIGHBITDEPTH) {
1100 motion_error = highbd_get_prediction_error(
1101 bsize, &x->plane[0].src, &xd->plane[0].pre[0], xd->bd);
1102 this_motion_error = highbd_get_prediction_error(
1103 bsize, &x->plane[0].src, &xd->plane[0].pre[0], 8);
1104 } else {
1105 motion_error =
1106 get_prediction_error(bsize, &x->plane[0].src, &xd->plane[0].pre[0]);
1107 this_motion_error = motion_error;
1108 }
1109#else
1110 motion_error =
1111 get_prediction_error(bsize, &x->plane[0].src, &xd->plane[0].pre[0]);
1112 this_motion_error = motion_error;
1113#endif // CONFIG_VP9_HIGHBITDEPTH
1114
1115 // Compute the motion error of the 0,0 motion using the last source
1116 // frame as the reference. Skip the further motion search on
1117 // reconstructed frame if this error is very small.
1118 unscaled_last_source_buf_2d.buf =
1119 cpi->unscaled_last_source->y_buffer + recon_yoffset;
1120 unscaled_last_source_buf_2d.stride = cpi->unscaled_last_source->y_stride;
1121#if CONFIG_VP9_HIGHBITDEPTH
1122 if (xd->cur_buf->flags & YV12_FLAG_HIGHBITDEPTH) {
1123 raw_motion_error = highbd_get_prediction_error(
1124 bsize, &x->plane[0].src, &unscaled_last_source_buf_2d, xd->bd);
1125 } else {
1126 raw_motion_error = get_prediction_error(bsize, &x->plane[0].src,
1127 &unscaled_last_source_buf_2d);
1128 }
1129#else
1130 raw_motion_error = get_prediction_error(bsize, &x->plane[0].src,
1131 &unscaled_last_source_buf_2d);
1132#endif // CONFIG_VP9_HIGHBITDEPTH
1133
1134 if (raw_motion_error > NZ_MOTION_PENALTY) {
1135 // Test last reference frame using the previous best mv as the
1136 // starting point (best reference) for the search.
1137 first_pass_motion_search(cpi, x, best_ref_mv, &mv, &motion_error);
1138
1139 v_fn_ptr.vf = get_block_variance_fn(bsize);
1140#if CONFIG_VP9_HIGHBITDEPTH
1141 if (xd->cur_buf->flags & YV12_FLAG_HIGHBITDEPTH) {
1142 v_fn_ptr.vf = highbd_get_block_variance_fn(bsize, 8);
1143 }
1144#endif // CONFIG_VP9_HIGHBITDEPTH
1145 this_motion_error =
1146 vp9_get_mvpred_var(x, &mv, best_ref_mv, &v_fn_ptr, 0);
1147
1148 // If the current best reference mv is not centered on 0,0 then do a
1149 // 0,0 based search as well.
1150 if (!is_zero_mv(best_ref_mv)) {
1151 tmp_err = INT_MAX;
1152 first_pass_motion_search(cpi, x, &zero_mv, &tmp_mv, &tmp_err);
1153
1154 if (tmp_err < motion_error) {
1155 motion_error = tmp_err;
1156 mv = tmp_mv;
1157 this_motion_error =
1158 vp9_get_mvpred_var(x, &tmp_mv, &zero_mv, &v_fn_ptr, 0);
1159 }
1160 }
1161#if CONFIG_RATE_CTRL
1162 store_fp_motion_vector(cpi, &mv, mb_row, mb_col, LAST_FRAME, 0);
1163#endif // CONFIG_RAGE_CTRL
1164
1165 // Search in an older reference frame.
1166 if ((cm->current_video_frame > 1) && gld_yv12 != NULL) {
1167 // Assume 0,0 motion with no mv overhead.
1168 int gf_motion_error;
1169
1170 xd->plane[0].pre[0].buf = gld_yv12->y_buffer + recon_yoffset;
1171#if CONFIG_VP9_HIGHBITDEPTH
1172 if (xd->cur_buf->flags & YV12_FLAG_HIGHBITDEPTH) {
1173 gf_motion_error = highbd_get_prediction_error(
1174 bsize, &x->plane[0].src, &xd->plane[0].pre[0], xd->bd);
1175 } else {
1176 gf_motion_error = get_prediction_error(bsize, &x->plane[0].src,
1177 &xd->plane[0].pre[0]);
1178 }
1179#else
1180 gf_motion_error = get_prediction_error(bsize, &x->plane[0].src,
1181 &xd->plane[0].pre[0]);
1182#endif // CONFIG_VP9_HIGHBITDEPTH
1183
1184 first_pass_motion_search(cpi, x, &zero_mv, &tmp_mv, &gf_motion_error);
1185#if CONFIG_RATE_CTRL
1186 store_fp_motion_vector(cpi, &tmp_mv, mb_row, mb_col, GOLDEN_FRAME, 1);
1187#endif // CONFIG_RAGE_CTRL
1188
1189 if (gf_motion_error < motion_error && gf_motion_error < this_error)
1190 ++(fp_acc_data->second_ref_count);
1191
1192 // Reset to last frame as reference buffer.
1193 xd->plane[0].pre[0].buf = first_ref_buf->y_buffer + recon_yoffset;
1194 xd->plane[1].pre[0].buf = first_ref_buf->u_buffer + recon_uvoffset;
1195 xd->plane[2].pre[0].buf = first_ref_buf->v_buffer + recon_uvoffset;
1196
1197 // In accumulating a score for the older reference frame take the
1198 // best of the motion predicted score and the intra coded error
1199 // (just as will be done for) accumulation of "coded_error" for
1200 // the last frame.
1201 if (gf_motion_error < this_error)
1202 fp_acc_data->sr_coded_error += gf_motion_error;
1203 else
1204 fp_acc_data->sr_coded_error += this_error;
1205 } else {
1206 fp_acc_data->sr_coded_error += motion_error;
1207 }
1208 } else {
1209 fp_acc_data->sr_coded_error += motion_error;
1210 }
1211
1212 // Start by assuming that intra mode is best.
1213 best_ref_mv->row = 0;
1214 best_ref_mv->col = 0;
1215
1216#if CONFIG_FP_MB_STATS
1217 if (cpi->use_fp_mb_stats) {
1218 // intra prediction statistics
1219 cpi->twopass.frame_mb_stats_buf[mb_index] = 0;
1220 cpi->twopass.frame_mb_stats_buf[mb_index] |= FPMB_DCINTRA_MASK;
1221 cpi->twopass.frame_mb_stats_buf[mb_index] |= FPMB_MOTION_ZERO_MASK;
1222 if (this_error > FPMB_ERROR_LARGE_TH) {
1223 cpi->twopass.frame_mb_stats_buf[mb_index] |= FPMB_ERROR_LARGE_MASK;
1224 } else if (this_error < FPMB_ERROR_SMALL_TH) {
1225 cpi->twopass.frame_mb_stats_buf[mb_index] |= FPMB_ERROR_SMALL_MASK;
1226 }
1227 }
1228#endif
1229
1230 if (motion_error <= this_error) {
1231 vpx_clear_system_state();
1232
1233 // Keep a count of cases where the inter and intra were very close
1234 // and very low. This helps with scene cut detection for example in
1235 // cropped clips with black bars at the sides or top and bottom.
1236 if (((this_error - intrapenalty) * 9 <= motion_error * 10) &&
1237 (this_error < (2 * intrapenalty))) {
1238 fp_acc_data->neutral_count += 1.0;
1239 if (cpi->row_mt_bit_exact)
1240 cpi->twopass.fp_mb_float_stats[mb_index].frame_mb_neutral_count =
1241 1.0;
1242 // Also track cases where the intra is not much worse than the inter
1243 // and use this in limiting the GF/arf group length.
1244 } else if ((this_error > NCOUNT_INTRA_THRESH) &&
1245 (this_error < (NCOUNT_INTRA_FACTOR * motion_error))) {
1246 mb_neutral_count =
1247 (double)motion_error / DOUBLE_DIVIDE_CHECK((double)this_error);
1248 fp_acc_data->neutral_count += mb_neutral_count;
1249 if (cpi->row_mt_bit_exact)
1250 cpi->twopass.fp_mb_float_stats[mb_index].frame_mb_neutral_count =
1251 mb_neutral_count;
1252 }
1253
1254 mv.row *= 8;
1255 mv.col *= 8;
1256 this_error = motion_error;
1257 xd->mi[0]->mode = NEWMV;
1258 xd->mi[0]->mv[0].as_mv = mv;
1259 xd->mi[0]->tx_size = TX_4X4;
1260 xd->mi[0]->ref_frame[0] = LAST_FRAME;
1261 xd->mi[0]->ref_frame[1] = NONE;
1262 vp9_build_inter_predictors_sby(xd, mb_row << 1, mb_col << 1, bsize);
1263 vp9_encode_sby_pass1(x, bsize);
1264 fp_acc_data->sum_mvr += mv.row;
1265 fp_acc_data->sum_mvr_abs += abs(mv.row);
1266 fp_acc_data->sum_mvc += mv.col;
1267 fp_acc_data->sum_mvc_abs += abs(mv.col);
1268 fp_acc_data->sum_mvrs += mv.row * mv.row;
1269 fp_acc_data->sum_mvcs += mv.col * mv.col;
1270 ++(fp_acc_data->intercount);
1271
1272 *best_ref_mv = mv;
1273
1274#if CONFIG_FP_MB_STATS
1275 if (cpi->use_fp_mb_stats) {
1276 // inter prediction statistics
1277 cpi->twopass.frame_mb_stats_buf[mb_index] = 0;
1278 cpi->twopass.frame_mb_stats_buf[mb_index] &= ~FPMB_DCINTRA_MASK;
1279 cpi->twopass.frame_mb_stats_buf[mb_index] |= FPMB_MOTION_ZERO_MASK;
1280 if (this_error > FPMB_ERROR_LARGE_TH) {
1281 cpi->twopass.frame_mb_stats_buf[mb_index] |= FPMB_ERROR_LARGE_MASK;
1282 } else if (this_error < FPMB_ERROR_SMALL_TH) {
1283 cpi->twopass.frame_mb_stats_buf[mb_index] |= FPMB_ERROR_SMALL_MASK;
1284 }
1285 }
1286#endif
1287
1288 if (!is_zero_mv(&mv)) {
1289 ++(fp_acc_data->mvcount);
1290
1291#if CONFIG_FP_MB_STATS
1292 if (cpi->use_fp_mb_stats) {
1293 cpi->twopass.frame_mb_stats_buf[mb_index] &= ~FPMB_MOTION_ZERO_MASK;
1294 // check estimated motion direction
1295 if (mv.as_mv.col > 0 && mv.as_mv.col >= abs(mv.as_mv.row)) {
1296 // right direction
1297 cpi->twopass.frame_mb_stats_buf[mb_index] |=
1298 FPMB_MOTION_RIGHT_MASK;
1299 } else if (mv.as_mv.row < 0 &&
1300 abs(mv.as_mv.row) >= abs(mv.as_mv.col)) {
1301 // up direction
1302 cpi->twopass.frame_mb_stats_buf[mb_index] |= FPMB_MOTION_UP_MASK;
1303 } else if (mv.as_mv.col < 0 &&
1304 abs(mv.as_mv.col) >= abs(mv.as_mv.row)) {
1305 // left direction
1306 cpi->twopass.frame_mb_stats_buf[mb_index] |=
1307 FPMB_MOTION_LEFT_MASK;
1308 } else {
1309 // down direction
1310 cpi->twopass.frame_mb_stats_buf[mb_index] |=
1311 FPMB_MOTION_DOWN_MASK;
1312 }
1313 }
1314#endif
1315 // Does the row vector point inwards or outwards?
1316 if (mb_row < cm->mb_rows / 2) {
1317 if (mv.row > 0)
1318 --(fp_acc_data->sum_in_vectors);
1319 else if (mv.row < 0)
1320 ++(fp_acc_data->sum_in_vectors);
1321 } else if (mb_row > cm->mb_rows / 2) {
1322 if (mv.row > 0)
1323 ++(fp_acc_data->sum_in_vectors);
1324 else if (mv.row < 0)
1325 --(fp_acc_data->sum_in_vectors);
1326 }
1327
1328 // Does the col vector point inwards or outwards?
1329 if (mb_col < cm->mb_cols / 2) {
1330 if (mv.col > 0)
1331 --(fp_acc_data->sum_in_vectors);
1332 else if (mv.col < 0)
1333 ++(fp_acc_data->sum_in_vectors);
1334 } else if (mb_col > cm->mb_cols / 2) {
1335 if (mv.col > 0)
1336 ++(fp_acc_data->sum_in_vectors);
1337 else if (mv.col < 0)
1338 --(fp_acc_data->sum_in_vectors);
1339 }
1340 }
1341 if (this_intra_error < scaled_low_intra_thresh) {
1342 fp_acc_data->frame_noise_energy += fp_estimate_block_noise(x, bsize);
1343 } else {
1344 fp_acc_data->frame_noise_energy += (int64_t)SECTION_NOISE_DEF;
1345 }
1346 } else { // Intra < inter error
1347 if (this_intra_error < scaled_low_intra_thresh) {
1348 fp_acc_data->frame_noise_energy += fp_estimate_block_noise(x, bsize);
1349 if (this_motion_error < scaled_low_intra_thresh) {
1350 fp_acc_data->intra_count_low += 1.0;
1351 } else {
1352 fp_acc_data->intra_count_high += 1.0;
1353 }
1354 } else {
1355 fp_acc_data->frame_noise_energy += (int64_t)SECTION_NOISE_DEF;
1356 fp_acc_data->intra_count_high += 1.0;
1357 }
1358 }
1359 } else {
1360 fp_acc_data->sr_coded_error += (int64_t)this_error;
1361#if CONFIG_RATE_CTRL
1362 store_fp_motion_vector(cpi, NULL, mb_row, mb_col, INTRA_FRAME, 0);
1363#endif // CONFIG_RAGE_CTRL
1364 }
1365 fp_acc_data->coded_error += (int64_t)this_error;
1366
1367 recon_yoffset += 16;
1368 recon_uvoffset += uv_mb_height;
1369
1370 // Accumulate row level stats to the corresponding tile stats
1371 if (cpi->row_mt && mb_col == mb_col_end - 1)
1372 accumulate_fp_mb_row_stat(tile_data, fp_acc_data);
1373
1374 (*(cpi->row_mt_sync_write_ptr))(&tile_data->row_mt_sync, mb_row, c,
1375 num_mb_cols);
1376 }
1377 vpx_clear_system_state();
1378}
1379
1380static void first_pass_encode(VP9_COMP *cpi, FIRSTPASS_DATA *fp_acc_data) {
1381 VP9_COMMON *const cm = &cpi->common;
1382 int mb_row;
1383 TileDataEnc tile_data;
1384 TileInfo *tile = &tile_data.tile_info;
1385 MV zero_mv = { 0, 0 };
1386 MV best_ref_mv;
1387 // Tiling is ignored in the first pass.
1388 vp9_tile_init(tile, cm, 0, 0);
1389
1390#if CONFIG_RATE_CTRL
1391 fp_motion_vector_info_reset(cpi->frame_info.frame_width,
1392 cpi->frame_info.frame_height,
1393 cpi->fp_motion_vector_info);
1394#endif
1395
1396 for (mb_row = 0; mb_row < cm->mb_rows; ++mb_row) {
1397 best_ref_mv = zero_mv;
1398 vp9_first_pass_encode_tile_mb_row(cpi, &cpi->td, fp_acc_data, &tile_data,
1399 &best_ref_mv, mb_row);
1400 }
1401}
1402
1403void vp9_first_pass(VP9_COMP *cpi, const struct lookahead_entry *source) {
1404 MACROBLOCK *const x = &cpi->td.mb;
1405 VP9_COMMON *const cm = &cpi->common;
1406 MACROBLOCKD *const xd = &x->e_mbd;
1407 TWO_PASS *twopass = &cpi->twopass;
1408
1409 YV12_BUFFER_CONFIG *const lst_yv12 = get_ref_frame_buffer(cpi, LAST_FRAME);
1410 YV12_BUFFER_CONFIG *gld_yv12 = get_ref_frame_buffer(cpi, GOLDEN_FRAME);
1411 YV12_BUFFER_CONFIG *const new_yv12 = get_frame_new_buffer(cm);
1412 const YV12_BUFFER_CONFIG *first_ref_buf = lst_yv12;
1413
1414 BufferPool *const pool = cm->buffer_pool;
1415
1416 FIRSTPASS_DATA fp_temp_data;
1417 FIRSTPASS_DATA *fp_acc_data = &fp_temp_data;
1418
1419 vpx_clear_system_state();
1420 vp9_zero(fp_temp_data);
1421 fp_acc_data->image_data_start_row = INVALID_ROW;
1422
1423 // First pass code requires valid last and new frame buffers.
1424 assert(new_yv12 != NULL);
1425 assert(frame_is_intra_only(cm) || (lst_yv12 != NULL));
1426
1427#if CONFIG_FP_MB_STATS
1428 if (cpi->use_fp_mb_stats) {
1429 vp9_zero_array(cpi->twopass.frame_mb_stats_buf, cm->initial_mbs);
1430 }
1431#endif
1432
1433 set_first_pass_params(cpi);
1434 vp9_set_quantizer(cpi, find_fp_qindex(cm->bit_depth));
1435
1436 vp9_setup_block_planes(&x->e_mbd, cm->subsampling_x, cm->subsampling_y);
1437
1438 vp9_setup_src_planes(x, cpi->Source, 0, 0);
1439 vp9_setup_dst_planes(xd->plane, new_yv12, 0, 0);
1440
1441 if (!frame_is_intra_only(cm)) {
1442 vp9_setup_pre_planes(xd, 0, first_ref_buf, 0, 0, NULL);
1443 }
1444
1445 xd->mi = cm->mi_grid_visible;
1446 xd->mi[0] = cm->mi;
1447
1448 vp9_frame_init_quantizer(cpi);
1449
1450 x->skip_recode = 0;
1451
1452 vp9_init_mv_probs(cm);
1453 vp9_initialize_rd_consts(cpi);
1454
1455 cm->log2_tile_rows = 0;
1456
1457 if (cpi->row_mt_bit_exact && cpi->twopass.fp_mb_float_stats == NULL)
1458 CHECK_MEM_ERROR(
1459 cm, cpi->twopass.fp_mb_float_stats,
1460 vpx_calloc(cm->MBs * sizeof(*cpi->twopass.fp_mb_float_stats), 1));
1461
1462 {
1463 FIRSTPASS_STATS fps;
1464 TileDataEnc *first_tile_col;
1465 if (!cpi->row_mt) {
1466 cm->log2_tile_cols = 0;
1467 cpi->row_mt_sync_read_ptr = vp9_row_mt_sync_read_dummy;
1468 cpi->row_mt_sync_write_ptr = vp9_row_mt_sync_write_dummy;
1469 first_pass_encode(cpi, fp_acc_data);
1470 first_pass_stat_calc(cpi, &fps, fp_acc_data);
1471 } else {
1472 cpi->row_mt_sync_read_ptr = vp9_row_mt_sync_read;
1473 cpi->row_mt_sync_write_ptr = vp9_row_mt_sync_write;
1474 if (cpi->row_mt_bit_exact) {
1475 cm->log2_tile_cols = 0;
1476 vp9_zero_array(cpi->twopass.fp_mb_float_stats, cm->MBs);
1477 }
1478 vp9_encode_fp_row_mt(cpi);
1479 first_tile_col = &cpi->tile_data[0];
1480 if (cpi->row_mt_bit_exact)
1481 accumulate_floating_point_stats(cpi, first_tile_col);
1482 first_pass_stat_calc(cpi, &fps, &(first_tile_col->fp_data));
1483 }
1484
1485 // Dont allow a value of 0 for duration.
1486 // (Section duration is also defaulted to minimum of 1.0).
1487 fps.duration = VPXMAX(1.0, (double)(source->ts_end - source->ts_start));
1488
1489 // Don't want to do output stats with a stack variable!
1490 twopass->this_frame_stats = fps;
1491 output_stats(&twopass->this_frame_stats);
1492 accumulate_stats(&twopass->total_stats, &fps);
1493
1494#if CONFIG_FP_MB_STATS
1495 if (cpi->use_fp_mb_stats) {
1496 output_fpmb_stats(twopass->frame_mb_stats_buf, cm, cpi->output_pkt_list);
1497 }
1498#endif
1499 }
1500
1501 // Copy the previous Last Frame back into gf and and arf buffers if
1502 // the prediction is good enough... but also don't allow it to lag too far.
1503 if ((twopass->sr_update_lag > 3) ||
1504 ((cm->current_video_frame > 0) &&
1505 (twopass->this_frame_stats.pcnt_inter > 0.20) &&
1506 ((twopass->this_frame_stats.intra_error /
1507 DOUBLE_DIVIDE_CHECK(twopass->this_frame_stats.coded_error)) > 2.0))) {
1508 if (gld_yv12 != NULL) {
1509 ref_cnt_fb(pool->frame_bufs, &cm->ref_frame_map[cpi->gld_fb_idx],
1510 cm->ref_frame_map[cpi->lst_fb_idx]);
1511 }
1512 twopass->sr_update_lag = 1;
1513 } else {
1514 ++twopass->sr_update_lag;
1515 }
1516
1517 vpx_extend_frame_borders(new_yv12);
1518
1519 // The frame we just compressed now becomes the last frame.
1520 ref_cnt_fb(pool->frame_bufs, &cm->ref_frame_map[cpi->lst_fb_idx],
1521 cm->new_fb_idx);
1522
1523 // Special case for the first frame. Copy into the GF buffer as a second
1524 // reference.
1525 if (cm->current_video_frame == 0 && cpi->gld_fb_idx != INVALID_IDX) {
1526 ref_cnt_fb(pool->frame_bufs, &cm->ref_frame_map[cpi->gld_fb_idx],
1527 cm->ref_frame_map[cpi->lst_fb_idx]);
1528 }
1529
1530 // Use this to see what the first pass reconstruction looks like.
1531 if (0) {
1532 char filename[512];
1533 FILE *recon_file;
1534 snprintf(filename, sizeof(filename), "enc%04d.yuv",
1535 (int)cm->current_video_frame);
1536
1537 if (cm->current_video_frame == 0)
1538 recon_file = fopen(filename, "wb");
1539 else
1540 recon_file = fopen(filename, "ab");
1541
1542 (void)fwrite(lst_yv12->buffer_alloc, lst_yv12->frame_size, 1, recon_file);
1543 fclose(recon_file);
1544 }
1545
1546 // In the first pass, every frame is considered as a show frame.
1547 update_frame_indexes(cm, /*show_frame=*/1);
1548 if (cpi->use_svc) vp9_inc_frame_in_layer(cpi);
1549}
1550
1551static const double q_pow_term[(QINDEX_RANGE >> 5) + 1] = { 0.65, 0.70, 0.75,
1552 0.85, 0.90, 0.90,
1553 0.90, 1.00, 1.25 };
1554
1555static double calc_correction_factor(double err_per_mb, double err_divisor,
1556 int q) {
1557 const double error_term = err_per_mb / DOUBLE_DIVIDE_CHECK(err_divisor);
1558 const int index = q >> 5;
1559 double power_term;
1560
1561 assert((index >= 0) && (index < (QINDEX_RANGE >> 5)));
1562
1563 // Adjustment based on quantizer to the power term.
1564 power_term =
1565 q_pow_term[index] +
1566 (((q_pow_term[index + 1] - q_pow_term[index]) * (q % 32)) / 32.0);
1567
1568 // Calculate correction factor.
1569 if (power_term < 1.0) assert(error_term >= 0.0);
1570
1571 return fclamp(pow(error_term, power_term), 0.05, 5.0);
1572}
1573
1574static double wq_err_divisor(VP9_COMP *cpi) {
1575 const VP9_COMMON *const cm = &cpi->common;
1576 unsigned int screen_area = (cm->width * cm->height);
1577
1578 // Use a different error per mb factor for calculating boost for
1579 // different formats.
1580 if (screen_area <= 640 * 360) {
1581 return 115.0;
1582 } else if (screen_area < 1280 * 720) {
1583 return 125.0;
1584 } else if (screen_area <= 1920 * 1080) {
1585 return 130.0;
1586 } else if (screen_area < 3840 * 2160) {
1587 return 150.0;
1588 }
1589
1590 // Fall through to here only for 4K and above.
1591 return 200.0;
1592}
1593
1594#define NOISE_FACTOR_MIN 0.9
1595#define NOISE_FACTOR_MAX 1.1
1596static int get_twopass_worst_quality(VP9_COMP *cpi, const double section_err,
1597 double inactive_zone, double section_noise,
1598 int section_target_bandwidth) {
1599 const RATE_CONTROL *const rc = &cpi->rc;
1600 const VP9EncoderConfig *const oxcf = &cpi->oxcf;
1601 TWO_PASS *const twopass = &cpi->twopass;
1602 double last_group_rate_err;
1603
1604 // Clamp the target rate to VBR min / max limts.
1605 const int target_rate =
1606 vp9_rc_clamp_pframe_target_size(cpi, section_target_bandwidth);
1607 double noise_factor = pow((section_noise / SECTION_NOISE_DEF), 0.5);
1608 noise_factor = fclamp(noise_factor, NOISE_FACTOR_MIN, NOISE_FACTOR_MAX);
1609 inactive_zone = fclamp(inactive_zone, 0.0, 1.0);
1610
1611// TODO(jimbankoski): remove #if here or below when this has been
1612// well tested.
1613#if CONFIG_ALWAYS_ADJUST_BPM
1614 // based on recent history adjust expectations of bits per macroblock.
1615 last_group_rate_err =
1616 (double)twopass->rolling_arf_group_actual_bits /
1617 DOUBLE_DIVIDE_CHECK((double)twopass->rolling_arf_group_target_bits);
1618 last_group_rate_err = VPXMAX(0.25, VPXMIN(4.0, last_group_rate_err));
1619 twopass->bpm_factor *= (3.0 + last_group_rate_err) / 4.0;
1620 twopass->bpm_factor = VPXMAX(0.25, VPXMIN(4.0, twopass->bpm_factor));
1621#endif
1622
1623 if (target_rate <= 0) {
1624 return rc->worst_quality; // Highest value allowed
1625 } else {
1626 const int num_mbs = (cpi->oxcf.resize_mode != RESIZE_NONE)
1627 ? cpi->initial_mbs
1628 : cpi->common.MBs;
1629 const double active_pct = VPXMAX(0.01, 1.0 - inactive_zone);
1630 const int active_mbs = (int)VPXMAX(1, (double)num_mbs * active_pct);
1631 const double av_err_per_mb = section_err / active_pct;
1632 const double speed_term = 1.0 + 0.04 * oxcf->speed;
1633 const int target_norm_bits_per_mb =
1634 (int)(((uint64_t)target_rate << BPER_MB_NORMBITS) / active_mbs);
1635 int q;
1636
1637// TODO(jimbankoski): remove #if here or above when this has been
1638// well tested.
1639#if !CONFIG_ALWAYS_ADJUST_BPM
1640 // based on recent history adjust expectations of bits per macroblock.
1641 last_group_rate_err =
1642 (double)twopass->rolling_arf_group_actual_bits /
1643 DOUBLE_DIVIDE_CHECK((double)twopass->rolling_arf_group_target_bits);
1644 last_group_rate_err = VPXMAX(0.25, VPXMIN(4.0, last_group_rate_err));
1645 twopass->bpm_factor *= (3.0 + last_group_rate_err) / 4.0;
1646 twopass->bpm_factor = VPXMAX(0.25, VPXMIN(4.0, twopass->bpm_factor));
1647#endif
1648
1649 // Try and pick a max Q that will be high enough to encode the
1650 // content at the given rate.
1651 for (q = rc->best_quality; q < rc->worst_quality; ++q) {
1652 const double factor =
1653 calc_correction_factor(av_err_per_mb, wq_err_divisor(cpi), q);
1654 const int bits_per_mb = vp9_rc_bits_per_mb(
1655 INTER_FRAME, q,
1656 factor * speed_term * cpi->twopass.bpm_factor * noise_factor,
1657 cpi->common.bit_depth);
1658 if (bits_per_mb <= target_norm_bits_per_mb) break;
1659 }
1660
1661 // Restriction on active max q for constrained quality mode.
1662 if (cpi->oxcf.rc_mode == VPX_CQ) q = VPXMAX(q, oxcf->cq_level);
1663 return q;
1664 }
1665}
1666
1667static void setup_rf_level_maxq(VP9_COMP *cpi) {
1668 int i;
1669 RATE_CONTROL *const rc = &cpi->rc;
1670 for (i = INTER_NORMAL; i < RATE_FACTOR_LEVELS; ++i) {
1671 int qdelta = vp9_frame_type_qdelta(cpi, i, rc->worst_quality);
1672 rc->rf_level_maxq[i] = VPXMAX(rc->worst_quality + qdelta, rc->best_quality);
1673 }
1674}

1676static void init_subsampling(VP9_COMP *cpi) {
1677 const VP9_COMMON *const cm = &cpi->common;
1678 RATE_CONTROL *const rc = &cpi->rc;
1679 const int w = cm->width;
1680 const int h = cm->height;
1681 int i;
1682
1683 for (i = 0; i < FRAME_SCALE_STEPS; ++i) {
1684 // Note: Frames with odd-sized dimensions may result from this scaling.
1685 rc->frame_width[i] = (w * 16) / frame_scale_factor[i];
1686 rc->frame_height[i] = (h * 16) / frame_scale_factor[i];
1687 }
1688
1689 setup_rf_level_maxq(cpi);
1690}

1699void vp9_init_second_pass(VP9_COMP *cpi) {
1700 VP9EncoderConfig *const oxcf = &cpi->oxcf;
1701 RATE_CONTROL *const rc = &cpi->rc;
1702 TWO_PASS *const twopass = &cpi->twopass;
1703 double frame_rate;
1704 FIRSTPASS_STATS *stats;
1705
1706 zero_stats(&twopass->total_stats);
1707 zero_stats(&twopass->total_left_stats);
1708
1709 if (!twopass->stats_in_end) return;
1710
1711 stats = &twopass->total_stats;
1712
1713 *stats = *twopass->stats_in_end;
1714 twopass->total_left_stats = *stats;
1715
1716 // Scan the first pass file and calculate a modified score for each
1717 // frame that is used to distribute bits. The modified score is assumed
1718 // to provide a linear basis for bit allocation. I.e a frame A with a score
1719 // that is double that of frame B will be allocated 2x as many bits.
1720 {
1721 double modified_score_total = 0.0;
1722 const FIRSTPASS_STATS *s = twopass->stats_in;
1723 double av_err;
1724
1725 if (oxcf->vbr_corpus_complexity) {
1726 twopass->mean_mod_score = (double)oxcf->vbr_corpus_complexity / 10.0;
1727 av_err = get_distribution_av_err(cpi, twopass);
1728 } else {
1729 av_err = get_distribution_av_err(cpi, twopass);
1730 // The first scan is unclamped and gives a raw average.
1731 while (s < twopass->stats_in_end) {
1732 modified_score_total += calculate_mod_frame_score(cpi, oxcf, s, av_err);
1733 ++s;
1734 }
1735
1736 // The average error from this first scan is used to define the midpoint
1737 // error for the rate distribution function.
1738 twopass->mean_mod_score =
1739 modified_score_total / DOUBLE_DIVIDE_CHECK(stats->count);
1740 }
1741
1742 // Second scan using clamps based on the previous cycle average.
1743 // This may modify the total and average somewhat but we dont bother with
1744 // further itterations.
1745 modified_score_total = 0.0;
1746 s = twopass->stats_in;
1747 while (s < twopass->stats_in_end) {
1748 modified_score_total +=
1749 calculate_norm_frame_score(cpi, twopass, oxcf, s, av_err);
1750 ++s;
1751 }
1752 twopass->normalized_score_left = modified_score_total;
1753
1754 // If using Corpus wide VBR mode then update the clip target bandwidth to
1755 // reflect how the clip compares to the rest of the corpus.
1756 if (oxcf->vbr_corpus_complexity) {
1757 oxcf->target_bandwidth =
1758 (int64_t)((double)oxcf->target_bandwidth *
1759 (twopass->normalized_score_left / stats->count));
1760 }
1761
1762#if COMPLEXITY_STATS_OUTPUT
1763 {
1764 FILE *compstats;
1765 compstats = fopen("complexity_stats.stt", "a");
1766 fprintf(compstats, "%10.3lf\n",
1767 twopass->normalized_score_left / stats->count);
1768 fclose(compstats);
1769 }
1770#endif
1771 }
1772
1773 frame_rate = 10000000.0 * stats->count / stats->duration;
1774 // Each frame can have a different duration, as the frame rate in the source
1775 // isn't guaranteed to be constant. The frame rate prior to the first frame
1776 // encoded in the second pass is a guess. However, the sum duration is not.
1777 // It is calculated based on the actual durations of all frames from the
1778 // first pass.
1779 vp9_new_framerate(cpi, frame_rate);
1780 twopass->bits_left =
1781 (int64_t)(stats->duration * oxcf->target_bandwidth / 10000000.0);
1782
1783 // This variable monitors how far behind the second ref update is lagging.
1784 twopass->sr_update_lag = 1;
1785
1786 // Reset the vbr bits off target counters
1787 rc->vbr_bits_off_target = 0;
1788 rc->vbr_bits_off_target_fast = 0;
1789 rc->rate_error_estimate = 0;
1790
1791 // Static sequence monitor variables.
1792 twopass->kf_zeromotion_pct = 100;
1793 twopass->last_kfgroup_zeromotion_pct = 100;
1794
1795 // Initialize bits per macro_block estimate correction factor.
1796 twopass->bpm_factor = 1.0;
1797 // Initialize actual and target bits counters for ARF groups so that
1798 // at the start we have a neutral bpm adjustment.
1799 twopass->rolling_arf_group_target_bits = 1;
1800 twopass->rolling_arf_group_actual_bits = 1;
1801
1802 if (oxcf->resize_mode != RESIZE_NONE) {
1803 init_subsampling(cpi);
1804 }
1805
1806 // Initialize the arnr strangth adjustment to 0
1807 twopass->arnr_strength_adjustment = 0;
1808}
1809
1810#define SR_DIFF_PART 0.0015
1811#define INTRA_PART 0.005
1812#define DEFAULT_DECAY_LIMIT 0.75
1813#define LOW_SR_DIFF_TRHESH 0.1
1814#define SR_DIFF_MAX 128.0
1815#define LOW_CODED_ERR_PER_MB 10.0
1816#define NCOUNT_FRAME_II_THRESH 6.0
1817
1818static double get_sr_decay_rate(const FRAME_INFO *frame_info,
1819 const FIRSTPASS_STATS *frame) {
1820 double sr_diff = (frame->sr_coded_error - frame->coded_error);
1821 double sr_decay = 1.0;
1822 double modified_pct_inter;
1823 double modified_pcnt_intra;
1824 const double motion_amplitude_part =
1825 frame->pcnt_motion *
1826 ((frame->mvc_abs + frame->mvr_abs) /
1827 (frame_info->frame_height + frame_info->frame_width));
1828
1829 modified_pct_inter = frame->pcnt_inter;
1830 if ((frame->coded_error > LOW_CODED_ERR_PER_MB) &&
1831 ((frame->intra_error / DOUBLE_DIVIDE_CHECK(frame->coded_error)) <
1832 (double)NCOUNT_FRAME_II_THRESH)) {
1833 modified_pct_inter =
1834 frame->pcnt_inter + frame->pcnt_intra_low - frame->pcnt_neutral;
1835 }
1836 modified_pcnt_intra = 100 * (1.0 - modified_pct_inter);
1837
1838 if ((sr_diff > LOW_SR_DIFF_TRHESH)) {
1839 sr_diff = VPXMIN(sr_diff, SR_DIFF_MAX);
1840 sr_decay = 1.0 - (SR_DIFF_PART * sr_diff) - motion_amplitude_part -
1841 (INTRA_PART * modified_pcnt_intra);
1842 }
1843 return VPXMAX(sr_decay, DEFAULT_DECAY_LIMIT);
1844}
1845
1846// This function gives an estimate of how badly we believe the prediction
1847// quality is decaying from frame to frame.
1848static double get_zero_motion_factor(const FRAME_INFO *frame_info,
1849 const FIRSTPASS_STATS *frame_stats) {
1850 const double zero_motion_pct =
1851 frame_stats->pcnt_inter - frame_stats->pcnt_motion;
1852 double sr_decay = get_sr_decay_rate(frame_info, frame_stats);
1853 return VPXMIN(sr_decay, zero_motion_pct);
1854}
1855
1856#define ZM_POWER_FACTOR 0.75
1857
1858static double get_prediction_decay_rate(const FRAME_INFO *frame_info,
1859 const FIRSTPASS_STATS *frame_stats) {
1860 const double sr_decay_rate = get_sr_decay_rate(frame_info, frame_stats);
1861 const double zero_motion_factor =
1862 (0.95 * pow((frame_stats->pcnt_inter - frame_stats->pcnt_motion),
1863 ZM_POWER_FACTOR));
1864
1865 return VPXMAX(zero_motion_factor,
1866 (sr_decay_rate + ((1.0 - sr_decay_rate) * zero_motion_factor)));
1867}
1868
1869static int get_show_idx(const TWO_PASS *twopass) {
1870 return (int)(twopass->stats_in - twopass->stats_in_start);
1871}
1872// Function to test for a condition where a complex transition is followed
1873// by a static section. For example in slide shows where there is a fade
1874// between slides. This is to help with more optimal kf and gf positioning.
1875static int check_transition_to_still(const FIRST_PASS_INFO *first_pass_info,
1876 int show_idx, int still_interval) {
1877 int j;
1878 int num_frames = fps_get_num_frames(first_pass_info);
1879 if (show_idx + still_interval > num_frames) {
1880 return 0;
1881 }
1882
1883 // Look ahead a few frames to see if static condition persists...
1884 for (j = 0; j < still_interval; ++j) {
1885 const FIRSTPASS_STATS *stats =
1886 fps_get_frame_stats(first_pass_info, show_idx + j);
1887 if (stats->pcnt_inter - stats->pcnt_motion < 0.999) break;
1888 }
1889
1890 // Only if it does do we signal a transition to still.
1891 return j == still_interval;
1892}
1893
1894// This function detects a flash through the high relative pcnt_second_ref
1895// score in the frame following a flash frame. The offset passed in should
1896// reflect this.
1897static int detect_flash_from_frame_stats(const FIRSTPASS_STATS *frame_stats) {
1898 // What we are looking for here is a situation where there is a
1899 // brief break in prediction (such as a flash) but subsequent frames
1900 // are reasonably well predicted by an earlier (pre flash) frame.
1901 // The recovery after a flash is indicated by a high pcnt_second_ref
1902 // useage or a second ref coded error notabley lower than the last
1903 // frame coded error.
1904 if (frame_stats == NULL) {
1905 return 0;
1906 }
1907 return (frame_stats->sr_coded_error < frame_stats->coded_error) ||
1908 ((frame_stats->pcnt_second_ref > frame_stats->pcnt_inter) &&
1909 (frame_stats->pcnt_second_ref >= 0.5));
1910}
1911
1912static int detect_flash(const TWO_PASS *twopass, int offset) {
1913 const FIRSTPASS_STATS *const next_frame = read_frame_stats(twopass, offset);
1914 return detect_flash_from_frame_stats(next_frame);
1915}
1916
1917// Update the motion related elements to the GF arf boost calculation.
1918static void accumulate_frame_motion_stats(const FIRSTPASS_STATS *stats,
1919 double *mv_in_out,
1920 double *mv_in_out_accumulator,
1921 double *abs_mv_in_out_accumulator,
1922 double *mv_ratio_accumulator) {
1923 const double pct = stats->pcnt_motion;
1924
1925 // Accumulate Motion In/Out of frame stats.
1926 *mv_in_out = stats->mv_in_out_count * pct;
1927 *mv_in_out_accumulator += *mv_in_out;
1928 *abs_mv_in_out_accumulator += fabs(*mv_in_out);
1929
1930 // Accumulate a measure of how uniform (or conversely how random) the motion
1931 // field is (a ratio of abs(mv) / mv).
1932 if (pct > 0.05) {
1933 const double mvr_ratio =
1934 fabs(stats->mvr_abs) / DOUBLE_DIVIDE_CHECK(fabs(stats->MVr));
1935 const double mvc_ratio =
1936 fabs(stats->mvc_abs) / DOUBLE_DIVIDE_CHECK(fabs(stats->MVc));
1937
1938 *mv_ratio_accumulator +=
1939 pct * (mvr_ratio < stats->mvr_abs ? mvr_ratio : stats->mvr_abs);
1940 *mv_ratio_accumulator +=
1941 pct * (mvc_ratio < stats->mvc_abs ? mvc_ratio : stats->mvc_abs);
1942 }
1943}
1944
1945#define BASELINE_ERR_PER_MB 12500.0
1946#define GF_MAX_BOOST 96.0
1947static double calc_frame_boost(const FRAME_INFO *frame_info,
1948 const FIRSTPASS_STATS *this_frame,
1949 int avg_frame_qindex,
1950 double this_frame_mv_in_out) {
1951 double frame_boost;
1952 const double lq =
1953 vp9_convert_qindex_to_q(avg_frame_qindex, frame_info->bit_depth);
1954 const double boost_q_correction = VPXMIN((0.5 + (lq * 0.015)), 1.5);
1955 const double active_area = calculate_active_area(frame_info, this_frame);
1956
1957 // Underlying boost factor is based on inter error ratio.
1958 frame_boost = (BASELINE_ERR_PER_MB * active_area) /
1959 DOUBLE_DIVIDE_CHECK(this_frame->coded_error);
1960
1961 // Small adjustment for cases where there is a zoom out
1962 if (this_frame_mv_in_out > 0.0)
1963 frame_boost += frame_boost * (this_frame_mv_in_out * 2.0);
1964
1965 // Q correction and scalling
1966 frame_boost = frame_boost * boost_q_correction;
1967
1968 return VPXMIN(frame_boost, GF_MAX_BOOST * boost_q_correction);
1969}
1970
1971static double kf_err_per_mb(VP9_COMP *cpi) {
1972 const VP9_COMMON *const cm = &cpi->common;
1973 unsigned int screen_area = (cm->width * cm->height);
1974
1975 // Use a different error per mb factor for calculating boost for
1976 // different formats.
1977 if (screen_area < 1280 * 720) {
1978 return 2000.0;
1979 } else if (screen_area < 1920 * 1080) {
1980 return 500.0;
1981 }
1982 return 250.0;
1983}
1984
1985static double calc_kf_frame_boost(VP9_COMP *cpi,
1986 const FIRSTPASS_STATS *this_frame,
1987 double *sr_accumulator,
1988 double this_frame_mv_in_out,
1989 double max_boost) {
1990 double frame_boost;
1991 const double lq = vp9_convert_qindex_to_q(
1992 cpi->rc.avg_frame_qindex[INTER_FRAME], cpi->common.bit_depth);
1993 const double boost_q_correction = VPXMIN((0.50 + (lq * 0.015)), 2.00);
1994 const double active_area =
1995 calculate_active_area(&cpi->frame_info, this_frame);
1996
1997 // Underlying boost factor is based on inter error ratio.
1998 frame_boost = (kf_err_per_mb(cpi) * active_area) /
1999 DOUBLE_DIVIDE_CHECK(this_frame->coded_error + *sr_accumulator);
2000
2001 // Update the accumulator for second ref error difference.
2002 // This is intended to give an indication of how much the coded error is
2003 // increasing over time.
2004 *sr_accumulator += (this_frame->sr_coded_error - this_frame->coded_error);
2005 *sr_accumulator = VPXMAX(0.0, *sr_accumulator);
2006
2007 // Small adjustment for cases where there is a zoom out
2008 if (this_frame_mv_in_out > 0.0)
2009 frame_boost += frame_boost * (this_frame_mv_in_out * 2.0);
2010
2011 // Q correction and scaling
2012 // The 40.0 value here is an experimentally derived baseline minimum.
2013 // This value is in line with the minimum per frame boost in the alt_ref
2014 // boost calculation.
2015 frame_boost = ((frame_boost + 40.0) * boost_q_correction);
2016
2017 return VPXMIN(frame_boost, max_boost * boost_q_correction);
2018}
2019
2020static int compute_arf_boost(const FRAME_INFO *frame_info,
2021 const FIRST_PASS_INFO *first_pass_info,
2022 int arf_show_idx, int f_frames, int b_frames,
2023 int avg_frame_qindex) {
2024 int i;
2025 double boost_score = 0.0;
2026 double mv_ratio_accumulator = 0.0;
2027 double decay_accumulator = 1.0;
2028 double this_frame_mv_in_out = 0.0;
2029 double mv_in_out_accumulator = 0.0;
2030 double abs_mv_in_out_accumulator = 0.0;
2031 int arf_boost;
2032 int flash_detected = 0;
2033
2034 // Search forward from the proposed arf/next gf position.
2035 for (i = 0; i < f_frames; ++i) {
2036 const FIRSTPASS_STATS *this_frame =
2037 fps_get_frame_stats(first_pass_info, arf_show_idx + i);
2038 const FIRSTPASS_STATS *next_frame =
2039 fps_get_frame_stats(first_pass_info, arf_show_idx + i + 1);
2040 if (this_frame == NULL) break;
2041
2042 // Update the motion related elements to the boost calculation.
2043 accumulate_frame_motion_stats(
2044 this_frame, &this_frame_mv_in_out, &mv_in_out_accumulator,
2045 &abs_mv_in_out_accumulator, &mv_ratio_accumulator);
2046
2047 // We want to discount the flash frame itself and the recovery
2048 // frame that follows as both will have poor scores.
2049 flash_detected = detect_flash_from_frame_stats(this_frame) ||
2050 detect_flash_from_frame_stats(next_frame);
2051
2052 // Accumulate the effect of prediction quality decay.
2053 if (!flash_detected) {
2054 decay_accumulator *= get_prediction_decay_rate(frame_info, this_frame);
2055 decay_accumulator = decay_accumulator < MIN_DECAY_FACTOR
2056 ? MIN_DECAY_FACTOR
2057 : decay_accumulator;
2058 }
2059 boost_score += decay_accumulator * calc_frame_boost(frame_info, this_frame,
2060 avg_frame_qindex,
2061 this_frame_mv_in_out);
2062 }
2063
2064 arf_boost = (int)boost_score;
2065
2066 // Reset for backward looking loop.
2067 boost_score = 0.0;
2068 mv_ratio_accumulator = 0.0;
2069 decay_accumulator = 1.0;
2070 this_frame_mv_in_out = 0.0;
2071 mv_in_out_accumulator = 0.0;
2072 abs_mv_in_out_accumulator = 0.0;
2073
2074 // Search backward towards last gf position.
2075 for (i = -1; i >= -b_frames; --i) {
2076 const FIRSTPASS_STATS *this_frame =
2077 fps_get_frame_stats(first_pass_info, arf_show_idx + i);
2078 const FIRSTPASS_STATS *next_frame =
2079 fps_get_frame_stats(first_pass_info, arf_show_idx + i + 1);
2080 if (this_frame == NULL) break;
2081
2082 // Update the motion related elements to the boost calculation.
2083 accumulate_frame_motion_stats(
2084 this_frame, &this_frame_mv_in_out, &mv_in_out_accumulator,
2085 &abs_mv_in_out_accumulator, &mv_ratio_accumulator);
2086
2087 // We want to discount the the flash frame itself and the recovery
2088 // frame that follows as both will have poor scores.
2089 flash_detected = detect_flash_from_frame_stats(this_frame) ||
2090 detect_flash_from_frame_stats(next_frame);
2091
2092 // Cumulative effect of prediction quality decay.
2093 if (!flash_detected) {
2094 decay_accumulator *= get_prediction_decay_rate(frame_info, this_frame);
2095 decay_accumulator = decay_accumulator < MIN_DECAY_FACTOR
2096 ? MIN_DECAY_FACTOR
2097 : decay_accumulator;
2098 }
2099 boost_score += decay_accumulator * calc_frame_boost(frame_info, this_frame,
2100 avg_frame_qindex,
2101 this_frame_mv_in_out);
2102 }
2103 arf_boost += (int)boost_score;
2104
2105 if (arf_boost < ((b_frames + f_frames) * 40))
2106 arf_boost = ((b_frames + f_frames) * 40);
2107 arf_boost = VPXMAX(arf_boost, MIN_ARF_GF_BOOST);
2108
2109 return arf_boost;
2110}
2111
2112static int calc_arf_boost(VP9_COMP *cpi, int f_frames, int b_frames) {
2113 const FRAME_INFO *frame_info = &cpi->frame_info;
2114 TWO_PASS *const twopass = &cpi->twopass;
2115 const int avg_inter_frame_qindex = cpi->rc.avg_frame_qindex[INTER_FRAME];
2116 int arf_show_idx = get_show_idx(twopass);
2117 return compute_arf_boost(frame_info, &twopass->first_pass_info, arf_show_idx,
2118 f_frames, b_frames, avg_inter_frame_qindex);
2119}

2121// Calculate a section intra ratio used in setting max loop filter.
2122static int calculate_section_intra_ratio(const FIRSTPASS_STATS *begin,
2123 const FIRSTPASS_STATS *end,
2124 int section_length) {
2125 const FIRSTPASS_STATS *s = begin;
2126 double intra_error = 0.0;
2127 double coded_error = 0.0;
2128 int i = 0;
2129
2130 while (s < end && i < section_length) {
2131 intra_error += s->intra_error;
2132 coded_error += s->coded_error;
2133 ++s;
2134 ++i;
2135 }
2136
2137 return (int)(intra_error / DOUBLE_DIVIDE_CHECK(coded_error));
2138}
2139
2140// Calculate the total bits to allocate in this GF/ARF group.
2141static int64_t calculate_total_gf_group_bits(VP9_COMP *cpi,
2142 double gf_group_err) {
2143 VP9_COMMON *const cm = &cpi->common;
2144 const RATE_CONTROL *const rc = &cpi->rc;
2145 const TWO_PASS *const twopass = &cpi->twopass;
2146 const int max_bits = frame_max_bits(rc, &cpi->oxcf);
2147 int64_t total_group_bits;
2148 const int is_key_frame = frame_is_intra_only(cm);
2149 const int arf_active_or_kf = is_key_frame || rc->source_alt_ref_active;
2150 int gop_frames =
2151 rc->baseline_gf_interval + rc->source_alt_ref_pending - arf_active_or_kf;
2152
2153 // Calculate the bits to be allocated to the group as a whole.
2154 if ((twopass->kf_group_bits > 0) && (twopass->kf_group_error_left > 0.0)) {
2155 int key_frame_interval = rc->frames_since_key + rc->frames_to_key;
2156 int distance_from_next_key_frame =
2157 rc->frames_to_key -
2158 (rc->baseline_gf_interval + rc->source_alt_ref_pending);
2159 int max_gf_bits_bias = rc->avg_frame_bandwidth;
2160 double gf_interval_bias_bits_normalize_factor =
2161 (double)rc->baseline_gf_interval / 16;
2162 total_group_bits = (int64_t)(twopass->kf_group_bits *
2163 (gf_group_err / twopass->kf_group_error_left));
2164 // TODO(ravi): Experiment with different values of max_gf_bits_bias
2165 total_group_bits +=
2166 (int64_t)((double)distance_from_next_key_frame / key_frame_interval *
2167 max_gf_bits_bias * gf_interval_bias_bits_normalize_factor);
2168 } else {
2169 total_group_bits = 0;
2170 }
2171
2172 // Clamp odd edge cases.
2173 total_group_bits = (total_group_bits < 0)
2174 ? 0
2175 : (total_group_bits > twopass->kf_group_bits)
2176 ? twopass->kf_group_bits
2177 : total_group_bits;
2178
2179 // Clip based on user supplied data rate variability limit.
2180 if (total_group_bits > (int64_t)max_bits * gop_frames)
2181 total_group_bits = (int64_t)max_bits * gop_frames;
2182
2183 return total_group_bits;
2184}
2185
2186// Calculate the number bits extra to assign to boosted frames in a group.
2187static int calculate_boost_bits(int frame_count, int boost,
2188 int64_t total_group_bits) {
2189 int allocation_chunks;
2190
2191 // return 0 for invalid inputs (could arise e.g. through rounding errors)
2192 if (!boost || (total_group_bits <= 0) || (frame_count < 0)) return 0;
2193
2194 allocation_chunks = (frame_count * NORMAL_BOOST) + boost;
2195
2196 // Prevent overflow.
2197 if (boost > 1023) {
2198 int divisor = boost >> 10;
2199 boost /= divisor;
2200 allocation_chunks /= divisor;
2201 }
2202
2203 // Calculate the number of extra bits for use in the boosted frame or frames.
2204 return VPXMAX((int)(((int64_t)boost * total_group_bits) / allocation_chunks),
2205 0);
2206}
2207
2208// Used in corpus vbr: Calculates the total normalized group complexity score
2209// for a given number of frames starting at the current position in the stats
2210// file.
2211static double calculate_group_score(VP9_COMP *cpi, double av_score,
2212 int frame_count) {
2213 VP9EncoderConfig *const oxcf = &cpi->oxcf;
2214 TWO_PASS *const twopass = &cpi->twopass;
2215 const FIRSTPASS_STATS *s = twopass->stats_in;
2216 double score_total = 0.0;
2217 int i = 0;
2218
2219 // We dont ever want to return a 0 score here.
2220 if (frame_count == 0) return 1.0;
2221
2222 while ((i < frame_count) && (s < twopass->stats_in_end)) {
2223 score_total += calculate_norm_frame_score(cpi, twopass, oxcf, s, av_score);
2224 ++s;
2225 ++i;
2226 }
2227
2228 return score_total;
2229}

2231static void find_arf_order(VP9_COMP *cpi, GF_GROUP *gf_group,
2232 int *index_counter, int depth, int start, int end) {
2233 TWO_PASS *twopass = &cpi->twopass;
2234 const FIRSTPASS_STATS *const start_pos = twopass->stats_in;
2235 FIRSTPASS_STATS fpf_frame;
2236 const int mid = (start + end + 1) >> 1;
2237 const int min_frame_interval = 2;
2238 int idx;
2239
2240 // Process regular P frames
2241 if ((end - start < min_frame_interval) ||
2242 (depth > gf_group->allowed_max_layer_depth)) {
2243 for (idx = start; idx <= end; ++idx) {
2244 gf_group->update_type[*index_counter] = LF_UPDATE;
2245 gf_group->arf_src_offset[*index_counter] = 0;
2246 gf_group->frame_gop_index[*index_counter] = idx;
2247 gf_group->rf_level[*index_counter] = INTER_NORMAL;
2248 gf_group->layer_depth[*index_counter] = depth;
2249 gf_group->gfu_boost[*index_counter] = NORMAL_BOOST;
2250 ++(*index_counter);
2251 }
2252 gf_group->max_layer_depth = VPXMAX(gf_group->max_layer_depth, depth);
2253 return;
2254 }
2255
2256 assert(abs(mid - start) >= 1 && abs(mid - end) >= 1);
2257
2258 // Process ARF frame
2259 gf_group->layer_depth[*index_counter] = depth;
2260 gf_group->update_type[*index_counter] = ARF_UPDATE;
2261 gf_group->arf_src_offset[*index_counter] = mid - start;
2262 gf_group->frame_gop_index[*index_counter] = mid;
2263 gf_group->rf_level[*index_counter] = GF_ARF_LOW;
2264
2265 for (idx = 0; idx <= mid; ++idx)
2266 if (EOF == input_stats(twopass, &fpf_frame)) break;
2267
2268 gf_group->gfu_boost[*index_counter] =
2269 VPXMAX(MIN_ARF_GF_BOOST,
2270 calc_arf_boost(cpi, end - mid + 1, mid - start) >> depth);
2271
2272 reset_fpf_position(twopass, start_pos);
2273
2274 ++(*index_counter);
2275
2276 find_arf_order(cpi, gf_group, index_counter, depth + 1, start, mid - 1);
2277
2278 gf_group->update_type[*index_counter] = USE_BUF_FRAME;
2279 gf_group->arf_src_offset[*index_counter] = 0;
2280 gf_group->frame_gop_index[*index_counter] = mid;
2281 gf_group->rf_level[*index_counter] = INTER_NORMAL;
2282 gf_group->layer_depth[*index_counter] = depth;
2283 ++(*index_counter);
2284
2285 find_arf_order(cpi, gf_group, index_counter, depth + 1, mid + 1, end);
2286}

2288static INLINE void set_gf_overlay_frame_type(GF_GROUP *gf_group,
2289 int frame_index,
2290 int source_alt_ref_active) {
2291 if (source_alt_ref_active) {
2292 gf_group->update_type[frame_index] = OVERLAY_UPDATE;

2294 gf_group->layer_depth[frame_index] = MAX_ARF_LAYERS - 1;
2295 gf_group->gfu_boost[frame_index] = NORMAL_BOOST;

2297 gf_group->update_type[frame_index] = GF_UPDATE;
2298 gf_group->rf_level[frame_index] = GF_ARF_STD;
