2302
2303static void define_gf_group_structure(VP9_COMP *cpi) {
2304 RATE_CONTROL *const rc = &cpi->rc;
2305 TWO_PASS *const twopass = &cpi->twopass;
2306 GF_GROUP *const gf_group = &twopass->gf_group;
2307 int frame_index = 0;
2308 int key_frame = cpi->common.frame_type == KEY_FRAME;
2309 int layer_depth = 1;
2310 int gop_frames =
2311 rc->baseline_gf_interval - (key_frame || rc->source_alt_ref_pending);
2312
2313 gf_group->frame_start = cpi->common.current_video_frame;
2314 gf_group->frame_end = gf_group->frame_start + rc->baseline_gf_interval;
2315 gf_group->max_layer_depth = 0;
2316 gf_group->allowed_max_layer_depth = 0;
2317
2318 // For key frames the frame target rate is already set and it
2319 // is also the golden frame.
2320 // === [frame_index == 0] ===
2321 if (!key_frame)
2322 set_gf_overlay_frame_type(gf_group, frame_index, rc->source_alt_ref_active);
2323
2324 ++frame_index;
2325
2326 // === [frame_index == 1] ===
2327 if (rc->source_alt_ref_pending) {
2328 gf_group->update_type[frame_index] = ARF_UPDATE;
2329 gf_group->rf_level[frame_index] = GF_ARF_STD;
2330 gf_group->layer_depth[frame_index] = layer_depth;
2331 gf_group->arf_src_offset[frame_index] =
2332 (unsigned char)(rc->baseline_gf_interval - 1);
2333 gf_group->frame_gop_index[frame_index] = rc->baseline_gf_interval;
2334 gf_group->max_layer_depth = 1;
2335 ++frame_index;
2336 ++layer_depth;
2337 gf_group->allowed_max_layer_depth = cpi->oxcf.enable_auto_arf;
2338 }
2339
2340 find_arf_order(cpi, gf_group, &frame_index, layer_depth, 1, gop_frames);
2341
2342 set_gf_overlay_frame_type(gf_group, frame_index, rc->source_alt_ref_pending);
2343 gf_group->arf_src_offset[frame_index] = 0;
2344 gf_group->frame_gop_index[frame_index] = rc->baseline_gf_interval;
2345
2346 // Set the frame ops number.
2347 gf_group->gf_group_size = frame_index;
2348}
2349
2350static void allocate_gf_group_bits(VP9_COMP *cpi, int64_t gf_group_bits,
2351 int gf_arf_bits) {
2352 VP9EncoderConfig *const oxcf = &cpi->oxcf;
2353 RATE_CONTROL *const rc = &cpi->rc;
2354 TWO_PASS *const twopass = &cpi->twopass;
2355 GF_GROUP *const gf_group = &twopass->gf_group;
2356 FIRSTPASS_STATS frame_stats;
2357 int i;
2358 int frame_index = 0;
2359 int target_frame_size;
2360 int key_frame;
2361 const int max_bits = frame_max_bits(&cpi->rc, oxcf);
2362 int64_t total_group_bits = gf_group_bits;
2363 int mid_frame_idx;
2364 int normal_frames;
2365 int normal_frame_bits;
2366 int last_frame_reduction = 0;
2367 double av_score = 1.0;
2368 double tot_norm_frame_score = 1.0;
2369 double this_frame_score = 1.0;
2370
2371 // Define the GF structure and specify
2372 int gop_frames = gf_group->gf_group_size;
2373
2374 key_frame = cpi->common.frame_type == KEY_FRAME;
2375
2376 // For key frames the frame target rate is already set and it
2377 // is also the golden frame.
2378 // === [frame_index == 0] ===
2379 if (!key_frame) {
2380 gf_group->bit_allocation[frame_index] =
2381 rc->source_alt_ref_active ? 0 : gf_arf_bits;
2382 }
2383
2384 // Deduct the boost bits for arf (or gf if it is not a key frame)
2385 // from the group total.
2386 if (rc->source_alt_ref_pending || !key_frame) total_group_bits -= gf_arf_bits;
2387
2388 ++frame_index;
2389
2390 // === [frame_index == 1] ===
2391 // Store the bits to spend on the ARF if there is one.
2392 if (rc->source_alt_ref_pending) {
2393 gf_group->bit_allocation[frame_index] = gf_arf_bits;
2394
2395 ++frame_index;
2396 }
2397
2398 // Define middle frame
2399 mid_frame_idx = frame_index + (rc->baseline_gf_interval >> 1) - 1;
2400
2401 normal_frames = (rc->baseline_gf_interval - 1);
2402 if (normal_frames > 1)
2403 normal_frame_bits = (int)(total_group_bits / normal_frames);
2404 else
2405 normal_frame_bits = (int)total_group_bits;
2406
2407 gf_group->gfu_boost[1] = rc->gfu_boost;
2408
2409 if (cpi->multi_layer_arf) {
2410 int idx;
2411 int arf_depth_bits[MAX_ARF_LAYERS] = { 0 };
2412 int arf_depth_count[MAX_ARF_LAYERS] = { 0 };
2413 int arf_depth_boost[MAX_ARF_LAYERS] = { 0 };
2414 int total_arfs = 1; // Account for the base layer ARF.
2415
2416 for (idx = 0; idx < gop_frames; ++idx) {
2417 if (gf_group->update_type[idx] == ARF_UPDATE) {
2418 arf_depth_boost[gf_group->layer_depth[idx]] += gf_group->gfu_boost[idx];
2419 ++arf_depth_count[gf_group->layer_depth[idx]];
2420 }
2421 }
2422
2423 for (idx = 2; idx < MAX_ARF_LAYERS; ++idx) {
2424 if (arf_depth_boost[idx] == 0) break;
2425 arf_depth_bits[idx] = calculate_boost_bits(
2426 rc->baseline_gf_interval - total_arfs - arf_depth_count[idx],
2427 arf_depth_boost[idx], total_group_bits);
2428
2429 total_group_bits -= arf_depth_bits[idx];
2430 total_arfs += arf_depth_count[idx];
2431 }
2432
2433 // offset the base layer arf
2434 normal_frames -= (total_arfs - 1);
2435 if (normal_frames > 1)
2436 normal_frame_bits = (int)(total_group_bits / normal_frames);
2437 else
2438 normal_frame_bits = (int)total_group_bits;
2439
2440 target_frame_size = normal_frame_bits;
2441 target_frame_size =
2442 clamp(target_frame_size, 0, VPXMIN(max_bits, (int)total_group_bits));
2443
2444 // The first layer ARF has its bit allocation assigned.
2445 for (idx = frame_index; idx < gop_frames; ++idx) {
2446 switch (gf_group->update_type[idx]) {
2447 case ARF_UPDATE:
2448 gf_group->bit_allocation[idx] =
2449 (int)(((int64_t)arf_depth_bits[gf_group->layer_depth[idx]] *
2450 gf_group->gfu_boost[idx]) /
2451 arf_depth_boost[gf_group->layer_depth[idx]]);
2452 break;
2453 case USE_BUF_FRAME: gf_group->bit_allocation[idx] = 0; break;
2454 default: gf_group->bit_allocation[idx] = target_frame_size; break;
2455 }
2456 }
2457 gf_group->bit_allocation[idx] = 0;
2458
2459 return;
2460 }
2461
2462 if (oxcf->vbr_corpus_complexity) {
2463 av_score = get_distribution_av_err(cpi, twopass);
2464 tot_norm_frame_score = calculate_group_score(cpi, av_score, normal_frames);
2465 }
2466
2467 // Allocate bits to the other frames in the group.
2468 for (i = 0; i < normal_frames; ++i) {
2469 if (EOF == input_stats(twopass, &frame_stats)) break;
2470 if (oxcf->vbr_corpus_complexity) {
2471 this_frame_score = calculate_norm_frame_score(cpi, twopass, oxcf,
2472 &frame_stats, av_score);
2473 normal_frame_bits = (int)((double)total_group_bits *
2474 (this_frame_score / tot_norm_frame_score));
2475 }
2476
2477 target_frame_size = normal_frame_bits;
2478 if ((i == (normal_frames - 1)) && (i >= 1)) {
2479 last_frame_reduction = normal_frame_bits / 16;
2480 target_frame_size -= last_frame_reduction;
2481 }
2482
2483 target_frame_size =
2484 clamp(target_frame_size, 0, VPXMIN(max_bits, (int)total_group_bits));
2485
2486 gf_group->bit_allocation[frame_index] = target_frame_size;
2487 ++frame_index;
2488 }
2489
2490 // Add in some extra bits for the middle frame in the group.
2491 gf_group->bit_allocation[mid_frame_idx] += last_frame_reduction;
2492
2493 // Note:
2494 // We need to configure the frame at the end of the sequence + 1 that will be
2495 // the start frame for the next group. Otherwise prior to the call to
2496 // vp9_rc_get_second_pass_params() the data will be undefined.
2497}

2499// Adjusts the ARNF filter for a GF group.
2500static void adjust_group_arnr_filter(VP9_COMP *cpi, double section_noise,
2501 double section_inter,
2502 double section_motion) {
2503 TWO_PASS *const twopass = &cpi->twopass;
2504 double section_zeromv = section_inter - section_motion;
2505
2506 twopass->arnr_strength_adjustment = 0;
2507
2508 if (section_noise < 150) {
2509 twopass->arnr_strength_adjustment -= 1;
2510 if (section_noise < 75) twopass->arnr_strength_adjustment -= 1;
2511 } else if (section_noise > 250)
2512 twopass->arnr_strength_adjustment += 1;
2513
2514 if (section_zeromv > 0.50) twopass->arnr_strength_adjustment += 1;
2515}
2516
2517// Analyse and define a gf/arf group.
2518#define ARF_ABS_ZOOM_THRESH 4.0
2519
2520#define MAX_GF_BOOST 5400
2521
2522typedef struct RANGE {
2523 int min;
2524 int max;
2525} RANGE;
2526
2527/* get_gop_coding_frame_num() depends on several fields in RATE_CONTROL *rc as
2528 * follows.
2529 * Static fields:
2530 * (The following fields will remain unchanged after initialization of encoder.)
2531 * rc->static_scene_max_gf_interval
2532 * rc->min_gf_interval
2533 *
2534 * Dynamic fields:
2535 * (The following fields will be updated before or after coding each frame.)
2536 * rc->frames_to_key
2537 * rc->frames_since_key
2538 * rc->source_alt_ref_active
2539 *
2540 * Special case: if CONFIG_RATE_CTRL is true, the external arf indexes will
2541 * determine the arf position.
2542 *
2543 * TODO(angiebird): Separate the dynamic fields and static fields into two
2544 * structs.
2545 */
2546static int get_gop_coding_frame_num(
2547 int *use_alt_ref, const FRAME_INFO *frame_info,
2548 const FIRST_PASS_INFO *first_pass_info, const RATE_CONTROL *rc,
2549 int gf_start_show_idx, const RANGE *active_gf_interval,
2550 double gop_intra_factor, int lag_in_frames) {
2551 double loop_decay_rate = 1.00;
2552 double mv_ratio_accumulator = 0.0;
2553 double this_frame_mv_in_out = 0.0;
2554 double mv_in_out_accumulator = 0.0;
2555 double abs_mv_in_out_accumulator = 0.0;
2556 double sr_accumulator = 0.0;
2557 // Motion breakout threshold for loop below depends on image size.
2558 double mv_ratio_accumulator_thresh =
2559 (frame_info->frame_height + frame_info->frame_width) / 4.0;
2560 double zero_motion_accumulator = 1.0;
2561 int gop_coding_frames;
2562
2563 *use_alt_ref = 1;
2564 gop_coding_frames = 0;
2565 while (gop_coding_frames < rc->static_scene_max_gf_interval &&
2566 gop_coding_frames < rc->frames_to_key) {
2567 const FIRSTPASS_STATS *next_next_frame;
2568 const FIRSTPASS_STATS *next_frame;
2569 int flash_detected;
2570 ++gop_coding_frames;
2571
2572 next_frame = fps_get_frame_stats(first_pass_info,
2573 gf_start_show_idx + gop_coding_frames);
2574 if (next_frame == NULL) {
2575 break;
2576 }
2577
2578 // Test for the case where there is a brief flash but the prediction
2579 // quality back to an earlier frame is then restored.
2580 next_next_frame = fps_get_frame_stats(
2581 first_pass_info, gf_start_show_idx + gop_coding_frames + 1);
2582 flash_detected = detect_flash_from_frame_stats(next_next_frame);
2583
2584 // Update the motion related elements to the boost calculation.
2585 accumulate_frame_motion_stats(
2586 next_frame, &this_frame_mv_in_out, &mv_in_out_accumulator,
2587 &abs_mv_in_out_accumulator, &mv_ratio_accumulator);
2588
2589 // Monitor for static sections.
2590 if ((rc->frames_since_key + gop_coding_frames - 1) > 1) {
2591 zero_motion_accumulator =
2592 VPXMIN(zero_motion_accumulator,
2593 get_zero_motion_factor(frame_info, next_frame));
2594 }
2595
2596 // Accumulate the effect of prediction quality decay.
2597 if (!flash_detected) {
2598 double last_loop_decay_rate = loop_decay_rate;
2599 loop_decay_rate = get_prediction_decay_rate(frame_info, next_frame);
2600
2601 // Break clause to detect very still sections after motion. For example,
2602 // a static image after a fade or other transition.
2603 if (gop_coding_frames > rc->min_gf_interval && loop_decay_rate >= 0.999 &&
2604 last_loop_decay_rate < 0.9) {
2605 int still_interval = 5;
2606 if (check_transition_to_still(first_pass_info,
2607 gf_start_show_idx + gop_coding_frames,
2608 still_interval)) {
2609 *use_alt_ref = 0;
2610 break;
2611 }
2612 }
2613
2614 // Update the accumulator for second ref error difference.
2615 // This is intended to give an indication of how much the coded error is
2616 // increasing over time.
2617 if (gop_coding_frames == 1) {
2618 sr_accumulator += next_frame->coded_error;
2619 } else {
2620 sr_accumulator +=
2621 (next_frame->sr_coded_error - next_frame->coded_error);
2622 }
2623 }
2624
2625 // Break out conditions.
2626 // Break at maximum of active_gf_interval->max unless almost totally
2627 // static.
2628 //
2629 // Note that the addition of a test of rc->source_alt_ref_active is
2630 // deliberate. The effect of this is that after a normal altref group even
2631 // if the material is static there will be one normal length GF group
2632 // before allowing longer GF groups. The reason for this is that in cases
2633 // such as slide shows where slides are separated by a complex transition
2634 // such as a fade, the arf group spanning the transition may not be coded
2635 // at a very high quality and hence this frame (with its overlay) is a
2636 // poor golden frame to use for an extended group.
2637 if ((gop_coding_frames >= active_gf_interval->max) &&
2638 ((zero_motion_accumulator < 0.995) || (rc->source_alt_ref_active))) {
2639 break;
2640 }
2641 if (
2642 // Don't break out with a very short interval.
2643 (gop_coding_frames >= active_gf_interval->min) &&
2644 // If possible dont break very close to a kf
2645 ((rc->frames_to_key - gop_coding_frames) >= rc->min_gf_interval) &&
2646 (gop_coding_frames & 0x01) && (!flash_detected) &&
2647 ((mv_ratio_accumulator > mv_ratio_accumulator_thresh) ||
2648 (abs_mv_in_out_accumulator > ARF_ABS_ZOOM_THRESH) ||
2649 (sr_accumulator > gop_intra_factor * next_frame->intra_error))) {
2650 break;
2651 }
2652 }
2653 *use_alt_ref &= zero_motion_accumulator < 0.995;
2654 *use_alt_ref &= gop_coding_frames < lag_in_frames;
2655 *use_alt_ref &= gop_coding_frames >= rc->min_gf_interval;
2656 return gop_coding_frames;
2657}
2658
2659static RANGE get_active_gf_inverval_range(
2660 const FRAME_INFO *frame_info, const RATE_CONTROL *rc, int arf_active_or_kf,
2661 int gf_start_show_idx, int active_worst_quality, int last_boosted_qindex) {
2662 RANGE active_gf_interval;
2663#if CONFIG_RATE_CTRL
2664 (void)frame_info;
2665 (void)gf_start_show_idx;
2666 (void)active_worst_quality;
2667 (void)last_boosted_qindex;
2668 active_gf_interval.min = rc->min_gf_interval + arf_active_or_kf + 2;
2669
2670 active_gf_interval.max = 16 + arf_active_or_kf;
2671
2672 if ((active_gf_interval.max <= rc->frames_to_key) &&
2673 (active_gf_interval.max >= (rc->frames_to_key - rc->min_gf_interval))) {
2674 active_gf_interval.min = rc->frames_to_key / 2;
2675 active_gf_interval.max = rc->frames_to_key / 2;
2676 }
2677#else
2678 int int_max_q = (int)(vp9_convert_qindex_to_q(active_worst_quality,
2679 frame_info->bit_depth));
2680 int q_term = (gf_start_show_idx == 0)
2681 ? int_max_q / 32
2682 : (int)(vp9_convert_qindex_to_q(last_boosted_qindex,
2683 frame_info->bit_depth) /
2684 6);
2685 active_gf_interval.min =
2686 rc->min_gf_interval + arf_active_or_kf + VPXMIN(2, int_max_q / 200);
2687 active_gf_interval.min =
2688 VPXMIN(active_gf_interval.min, rc->max_gf_interval + arf_active_or_kf);
2689
2690 // The value chosen depends on the active Q range. At low Q we have
2691 // bits to spare and are better with a smaller interval and smaller boost.
2692 // At high Q when there are few bits to spare we are better with a longer
2693 // interval to spread the cost of the GF.
2694 active_gf_interval.max = 11 + arf_active_or_kf + VPXMIN(5, q_term);
2695
2696 // Force max GF interval to be odd.
2697 active_gf_interval.max = active_gf_interval.max | 0x01;
2698
2699 // We have: active_gf_interval.min <=
2700 // rc->max_gf_interval + arf_active_or_kf.
2701 if (active_gf_interval.max < active_gf_interval.min) {
2702 active_gf_interval.max = active_gf_interval.min;
2703 } else {
2704 active_gf_interval.max =
2705 VPXMIN(active_gf_interval.max, rc->max_gf_interval + arf_active_or_kf);
2706 }
2707
2708 // Would the active max drop us out just before the near the next kf?
2709 if ((active_gf_interval.max <= rc->frames_to_key) &&
2710 (active_gf_interval.max >= (rc->frames_to_key - rc->min_gf_interval))) {
2711 active_gf_interval.max = rc->frames_to_key / 2;
2712 }
2713 active_gf_interval.max =
2714 VPXMAX(active_gf_interval.max, active_gf_interval.min);
2715#endif
2716 return active_gf_interval;
2717}
2718
2719static int get_arf_layers(int multi_layer_arf, int max_layers,
2720 int coding_frame_num) {
2721 assert(max_layers <= MAX_ARF_LAYERS);
2722 if (multi_layer_arf) {
2723 int layers = 0;
2724 int i;
2725 for (i = coding_frame_num; i > 0; i >>= 1) {
2726 ++layers;
2727 }
2728 layers = VPXMIN(max_layers, layers);
2729 return layers;
2730 } else {
2731 return 1;
2732 }
2733}
2734
2735static void define_gf_group(VP9_COMP *cpi, int gf_start_show_idx) {
2736 VP9_COMMON *const cm = &cpi->common;
2737 RATE_CONTROL *const rc = &cpi->rc;
2738 VP9EncoderConfig *const oxcf = &cpi->oxcf;
2739 TWO_PASS *const twopass = &cpi->twopass;
2740 const FRAME_INFO *frame_info = &cpi->frame_info;
2741 const FIRST_PASS_INFO *first_pass_info = &twopass->first_pass_info;
2742 const FIRSTPASS_STATS *const start_pos = twopass->stats_in;
2743 int gop_coding_frames;
2744
2745 double gf_group_err = 0.0;
2746 double gf_group_raw_error = 0.0;
2747 double gf_group_noise = 0.0;
2748 double gf_group_skip_pct = 0.0;
2749 double gf_group_inactive_zone_rows = 0.0;
2750 double gf_group_inter = 0.0;
2751 double gf_group_motion = 0.0;
2752
2753 int allow_alt_ref = is_altref_enabled(cpi);
2754 int use_alt_ref;
2755
2756 int64_t gf_group_bits;
2757 int gf_arf_bits;
2758 const int is_key_frame = frame_is_intra_only(cm);
2759 // If this is a key frame or the overlay from a previous arf then
2760 // the error score / cost of this frame has already been accounted for.
2761 const int arf_active_or_kf = is_key_frame || rc->source_alt_ref_active;
2762 int is_alt_ref_flash = 0;
2763
2764 double gop_intra_factor;
2765 int gop_frames;
2766 RANGE active_gf_interval;
2767
2768 // Reset the GF group data structures unless this is a key
2769 // frame in which case it will already have been done.
2770 if (is_key_frame == 0) {
2771 vp9_zero(twopass->gf_group);
2772 }
2773
2774 vpx_clear_system_state();
2775
2776 active_gf_interval = get_active_gf_inverval_range(
2777 frame_info, rc, arf_active_or_kf, gf_start_show_idx,
2778 twopass->active_worst_quality, rc->last_boosted_qindex);
2779
2780 if (cpi->multi_layer_arf) {
2781 int arf_layers = get_arf_layers(cpi->multi_layer_arf, oxcf->enable_auto_arf,
2782 active_gf_interval.max);
2783 gop_intra_factor = 1.0 + 0.25 * arf_layers;
2784 } else {
2785 gop_intra_factor = 1.0;
2786 }
2787
2788#if CONFIG_RATE_CTRL
2789 {
2790 const GOP_COMMAND *gop_command = &cpi->encode_command.gop_command;
2791 assert(allow_alt_ref == 1);
2792 if (gop_command->use) {
2793 gop_coding_frames = gop_command_coding_frame_count(gop_command);
2794 use_alt_ref = gop_command->use_alt_ref;
2795 } else {
2796 gop_coding_frames = get_gop_coding_frame_num(
2797 &use_alt_ref, frame_info, first_pass_info, rc, gf_start_show_idx,
2798 &active_gf_interval, gop_intra_factor, cpi->oxcf.lag_in_frames);
2799 use_alt_ref &= allow_alt_ref;
2800 }
2801 }
2802#else
2803 gop_coding_frames = get_gop_coding_frame_num(
2804 &use_alt_ref, frame_info, first_pass_info, rc, gf_start_show_idx,
2805 &active_gf_interval, gop_intra_factor, cpi->oxcf.lag_in_frames);
2806 use_alt_ref &= allow_alt_ref;
2807#endif
2808
2809 // Was the group length constrained by the requirement for a new KF?
2810 rc->constrained_gf_group = (gop_coding_frames >= rc->frames_to_key) ? 1 : 0;
2811
2812 // Should we use the alternate reference frame.
2813 if (use_alt_ref) {
2814 const int f_frames =
2815 (rc->frames_to_key - gop_coding_frames >= gop_coding_frames - 1)
2816 ? gop_coding_frames - 1
2817 : VPXMAX(0, rc->frames_to_key - gop_coding_frames);
2818 const int b_frames = gop_coding_frames - 1;
2819 const int avg_inter_frame_qindex = rc->avg_frame_qindex[INTER_FRAME];
2820 // TODO(angiebird): figure out why arf's location is assigned this way
2821 const int arf_show_idx = VPXMIN(gf_start_show_idx + gop_coding_frames + 1,
2822 fps_get_num_frames(first_pass_info));
2823
2824 // Calculate the boost for alt ref.
2825 rc->gfu_boost =
2826 compute_arf_boost(frame_info, first_pass_info, arf_show_idx, f_frames,
2827 b_frames, avg_inter_frame_qindex);
2828 rc->source_alt_ref_pending = 1;
2829 } else {
2830 const int f_frames = gop_coding_frames - 1;
2831 const int b_frames = 0;
2832 const int avg_inter_frame_qindex = rc->avg_frame_qindex[INTER_FRAME];
2833 // TODO(angiebird): figure out why arf's location is assigned this way
2834 const int gld_show_idx =
2835 VPXMIN(gf_start_show_idx + 1, fps_get_num_frames(first_pass_info));
2836 const int arf_boost =
2837 compute_arf_boost(frame_info, first_pass_info, gld_show_idx, f_frames,
2838 b_frames, avg_inter_frame_qindex);
2839 rc->gfu_boost = VPXMIN(MAX_GF_BOOST, arf_boost);
2840 rc->source_alt_ref_pending = 0;
2841 }
2842
2843#define LAST_ALR_ACTIVE_BEST_QUALITY_ADJUSTMENT_FACTOR 0.2
2844 rc->arf_active_best_quality_adjustment_factor = 1.0;
2845 rc->arf_increase_active_best_quality = 0;
2846
2847 if (!is_lossless_requested(&cpi->oxcf)) {
2848 if (rc->frames_since_key >= rc->frames_to_key) {
2849 // Increase the active best quality in the second half of key frame
2850 // interval.
2851 rc->arf_active_best_quality_adjustment_factor =
2852 LAST_ALR_ACTIVE_BEST_QUALITY_ADJUSTMENT_FACTOR +
2853 (1.0 - LAST_ALR_ACTIVE_BEST_QUALITY_ADJUSTMENT_FACTOR) *
2854 (rc->frames_to_key - gop_coding_frames) /
2855 (VPXMAX(1, ((rc->frames_to_key + rc->frames_since_key) / 2 -
2856 gop_coding_frames)));
2857 rc->arf_increase_active_best_quality = 1;
2858 } else if ((rc->frames_to_key - gop_coding_frames) > 0) {
2859 // Reduce the active best quality in the first half of key frame interval.
2860 rc->arf_active_best_quality_adjustment_factor =
2861 LAST_ALR_ACTIVE_BEST_QUALITY_ADJUSTMENT_FACTOR +
2862 (1.0 - LAST_ALR_ACTIVE_BEST_QUALITY_ADJUSTMENT_FACTOR) *
2863 (rc->frames_since_key + gop_coding_frames) /
2864 (VPXMAX(1, (rc->frames_to_key + rc->frames_since_key) / 2 +
2865 gop_coding_frames));
2866 rc->arf_increase_active_best_quality = -1;
2867 }
2868 }
2869
2870#ifdef AGGRESSIVE_VBR
2871 // Limit maximum boost based on interval length.
2872 rc->gfu_boost = VPXMIN((int)rc->gfu_boost, gop_coding_frames * 140);
2873#else
2874 rc->gfu_boost = VPXMIN((int)rc->gfu_boost, gop_coding_frames * 200);
2875#endif
2876
2877 // Cap the ARF boost when perceptual quality AQ mode is enabled. This is
2878 // designed to improve the perceptual quality of high value content and to
2879 // make consistent quality across consecutive frames. It will hurt objective
2880 // quality.
2881 if (oxcf->aq_mode == PERCEPTUAL_AQ)
2882 rc->gfu_boost = VPXMIN(rc->gfu_boost, MIN_ARF_GF_BOOST);
2883
2884 rc->baseline_gf_interval = gop_coding_frames - rc->source_alt_ref_pending;
2885
2886 if (rc->source_alt_ref_pending)
2887 is_alt_ref_flash = detect_flash(twopass, rc->baseline_gf_interval);
2888
2889 {
2890 const double av_err = get_distribution_av_err(cpi, twopass);
2891 const double mean_mod_score = twopass->mean_mod_score;
2892 // If the first frame is a key frame or the overlay from a previous arf then
2893 // the error score / cost of this frame has already been accounted for.
2894 int start_idx = arf_active_or_kf ? 1 : 0;
2895 int j;
2896 for (j = start_idx; j < gop_coding_frames; ++j) {
2897 int show_idx = gf_start_show_idx + j;
2898 const FIRSTPASS_STATS *frame_stats =
2899 fps_get_frame_stats(first_pass_info, show_idx);
2900 // Accumulate error score of frames in this gf group.
2901 gf_group_err += calc_norm_frame_score(oxcf, frame_info, frame_stats,
2902 mean_mod_score, av_err);
2903 gf_group_raw_error += frame_stats->coded_error;
2904 gf_group_noise += frame_stats->frame_noise_energy;
2905 gf_group_skip_pct += frame_stats->intra_skip_pct;
2906 gf_group_inactive_zone_rows += frame_stats->inactive_zone_rows;
2907 gf_group_inter += frame_stats->pcnt_inter;
2908 gf_group_motion += frame_stats->pcnt_motion;
2909 }
2910 }
2911
2912 // Calculate the bits to be allocated to the gf/arf group as a whole
2913 gf_group_bits = calculate_total_gf_group_bits(cpi, gf_group_err);
2914
2915 gop_frames =
2916 rc->baseline_gf_interval + rc->source_alt_ref_pending - arf_active_or_kf;
2917
2918 // Store the average moise level measured for the group
2919 // TODO(any): Experiment with removal of else condition (gop_frames = 0) so
2920 // that consumption of group noise energy is based on previous gf group
2921 if (gop_frames > 0)
2922 twopass->gf_group.group_noise_energy = (int)(gf_group_noise / gop_frames);
2923 else
2924 twopass->gf_group.group_noise_energy = 0;
2925
2926 // Calculate an estimate of the maxq needed for the group.
2927 // We are more aggressive about correcting for sections
2928 // where there could be significant overshoot than for easier
2929 // sections where we do not wish to risk creating an overshoot
2930 // of the allocated bit budget.
2931 if ((cpi->oxcf.rc_mode != VPX_Q) && (rc->baseline_gf_interval > 1)) {
2932 const int vbr_group_bits_per_frame = (int)(gf_group_bits / gop_frames);
2933 const double group_av_err = gf_group_raw_error / gop_frames;
2934 const double group_av_noise = gf_group_noise / gop_frames;
2935 const double group_av_skip_pct = gf_group_skip_pct / gop_frames;
2936 const double group_av_inactive_zone = ((gf_group_inactive_zone_rows * 2) /
2937 (gop_frames * (double)cm->mb_rows));
2938 int tmp_q = get_twopass_worst_quality(
2939 cpi, group_av_err, (group_av_skip_pct + group_av_inactive_zone),
2940 group_av_noise, vbr_group_bits_per_frame);
2941 twopass->active_worst_quality =
2942 (tmp_q + (twopass->active_worst_quality * 3)) >> 2;
2943
2944#if CONFIG_ALWAYS_ADJUST_BPM
2945 // Reset rolling actual and target bits counters for ARF groups.
2946 twopass->rolling_arf_group_target_bits = 0;
2947 twopass->rolling_arf_group_actual_bits = 0;
2948#endif
2949 }
2950
2951 // Context Adjustment of ARNR filter strength
2952 if (rc->baseline_gf_interval > 1) {
2953 adjust_group_arnr_filter(cpi, (gf_group_noise / gop_frames),
2954 (gf_group_inter / gop_frames),
2955 (gf_group_motion / gop_frames));
2956 } else {
2957 twopass->arnr_strength_adjustment = 0;
2958 }
2959
2960 // Calculate the extra bits to be used for boosted frame(s)
2961 gf_arf_bits = calculate_boost_bits((rc->baseline_gf_interval - 1),
2962 rc->gfu_boost, gf_group_bits);
2963
2964 // Adjust KF group bits and error remaining.
2965 twopass->kf_group_error_left -= gf_group_err;
2966
2967 // Decide GOP structure.
2968 define_gf_group_structure(cpi);
2969
2970 // Allocate bits to each of the frames in the GF group.
2971 allocate_gf_group_bits(cpi, gf_group_bits, gf_arf_bits);
2972
2973 // Reset the file position.
2974 reset_fpf_position(twopass, start_pos);
2975
2976 // Calculate a section intra ratio used in setting max loop filter.
2977 twopass->section_intra_rating = calculate_section_intra_ratio(
2978 start_pos, twopass->stats_in_end, rc->baseline_gf_interval);
2979
2980 if (oxcf->resize_mode == RESIZE_DYNAMIC) {
2981 // Default to starting GF groups at normal frame size.
2982 cpi->rc.next_frame_size_selector = UNSCALED;
2983 }
2984#if !CONFIG_ALWAYS_ADJUST_BPM
2985 // Reset rolling actual and target bits counters for ARF groups.
2986 twopass->rolling_arf_group_target_bits = 0;
2987 twopass->rolling_arf_group_actual_bits = 0;
2988#endif
2989 rc->preserve_arf_as_gld = rc->preserve_next_arf_as_gld;
2990 rc->preserve_next_arf_as_gld = 0;
2991 // If alt ref frame is flash do not set preserve_arf_as_gld
2992 if (!is_lossless_requested(&cpi->oxcf) && !cpi->use_svc &&
2993 cpi->oxcf.aq_mode == NO_AQ && cpi->multi_layer_arf && !is_alt_ref_flash)
2994 rc->preserve_next_arf_as_gld = 1;
2995}
2996
2997// Intra / Inter threshold very low
2998#define VERY_LOW_II 1.5
2999// Clean slide transitions we expect a sharp single frame spike in error.
3000#define ERROR_SPIKE 5.0
3001
3002// Slide show transition detection.
3003// Tests for case where there is very low error either side of the current frame
3004// but much higher just for this frame. This can help detect key frames in
3005// slide shows even where the slides are pictures of different sizes.
3006// Also requires that intra and inter errors are very similar to help eliminate
3007// harmful false positives.
3008// It will not help if the transition is a fade or other multi-frame effect.
3009static int slide_transition(const FIRSTPASS_STATS *this_frame,
3010 const FIRSTPASS_STATS *last_frame,
3011 const FIRSTPASS_STATS *next_frame) {
3012 return (this_frame->intra_error < (this_frame->coded_error * VERY_LOW_II)) &&
3013 (this_frame->coded_error > (last_frame->coded_error * ERROR_SPIKE)) &&
3014 (this_frame->coded_error > (next_frame->coded_error * ERROR_SPIKE));
3015}
3016
3017// This test looks for anomalous changes in the nature of the intra signal
3018// related to the previous and next frame as an indicator for coding a key
3019// frame. This test serves to detect some additional scene cuts,
3020// especially in lowish motion and low contrast sections, that are missed
3021// by the other tests.
3022static int intra_step_transition(const FIRSTPASS_STATS *this_frame,
3023 const FIRSTPASS_STATS *last_frame,
3024 const FIRSTPASS_STATS *next_frame) {
3025 double last_ii_ratio;
3026 double this_ii_ratio;
3027 double next_ii_ratio;
3028 double last_pcnt_intra = 1.0 - last_frame->pcnt_inter;
3029 double this_pcnt_intra = 1.0 - this_frame->pcnt_inter;
3030 double next_pcnt_intra = 1.0 - next_frame->pcnt_inter;
3031 double mod_this_intra = this_pcnt_intra + this_frame->pcnt_neutral;
3032
3033 // Calculate ii ratio for this frame last frame and next frame.
3034 last_ii_ratio =
3035 last_frame->intra_error / DOUBLE_DIVIDE_CHECK(last_frame->coded_error);
3036 this_ii_ratio =
3037 this_frame->intra_error / DOUBLE_DIVIDE_CHECK(this_frame->coded_error);
3038 next_ii_ratio =
3039 next_frame->intra_error / DOUBLE_DIVIDE_CHECK(next_frame->coded_error);
3040
3041 // Return true the intra/inter ratio for the current frame is
3042 // low but better in the next and previous frame and the relative useage of
3043 // intra in the current frame is markedly higher than the last and next frame.
3044 if ((this_ii_ratio < 2.0) && (last_ii_ratio > 2.25) &&
3045 (next_ii_ratio > 2.25) && (this_pcnt_intra > (3 * last_pcnt_intra)) &&
3046 (this_pcnt_intra > (3 * next_pcnt_intra)) &&
3047 ((this_pcnt_intra > 0.075) || (mod_this_intra > 0.85))) {
3048 return 1;
3049 // Very low inter intra ratio (i.e. not much gain from inter coding), most
3050 // blocks neutral on coding method and better inter prediction either side
3051 } else if ((this_ii_ratio < 1.25) && (mod_this_intra > 0.85) &&
3052 (this_ii_ratio < last_ii_ratio * 0.9) &&
3053 (this_ii_ratio < next_ii_ratio * 0.9)) {
3054 return 1;
3055 } else {
3056 return 0;
3057 }
3058}
3059
3060// Minimum % intra coding observed in first pass (1.0 = 100%)
3061#define MIN_INTRA_LEVEL 0.25
3062// Threshold for use of the lagging second reference frame. Scene cuts do not
3063// usually have a high second ref useage.
3064#define SECOND_REF_USEAGE_THRESH 0.2
3065// Hard threshold where the first pass chooses intra for almost all blocks.
3066// In such a case even if the frame is not a scene cut coding a key frame
3067// may be a good option.
3068#define VERY_LOW_INTER_THRESH 0.05
3069// Maximum threshold for the relative ratio of intra error score vs best
3070// inter error score.
3071#define KF_II_ERR_THRESHOLD 2.5
3072#define KF_II_MAX 128.0
3073#define II_FACTOR 12.5
3074// Test for very low intra complexity which could cause false key frames
3075#define V_LOW_INTRA 0.5
3076
3077static int test_candidate_kf(const FIRST_PASS_INFO *first_pass_info,
3078 int show_idx) {
3079 const FIRSTPASS_STATS *last_frame =
3080 fps_get_frame_stats(first_pass_info, show_idx - 1);
3081 const FIRSTPASS_STATS *this_frame =
3082 fps_get_frame_stats(first_pass_info, show_idx);
3083 const FIRSTPASS_STATS *next_frame =
3084 fps_get_frame_stats(first_pass_info, show_idx + 1);
3085 int is_viable_kf = 0;
3086 double pcnt_intra = 1.0 - this_frame->pcnt_inter;
3087
3088 // Does the frame satisfy the primary criteria of a key frame?
3089 // See above for an explanation of the test criteria.
3090 // If so, then examine how well it predicts subsequent frames.
3091 detect_flash_from_frame_stats(next_frame);
3092 if (!detect_flash_from_frame_stats(this_frame) &&
3093 !detect_flash_from_frame_stats(next_frame) &&
3094 (this_frame->pcnt_second_ref < SECOND_REF_USEAGE_THRESH) &&
3095 ((this_frame->pcnt_inter < VERY_LOW_INTER_THRESH) ||
3096 (slide_transition(this_frame, last_frame, next_frame)) ||
3097 (intra_step_transition(this_frame, last_frame, next_frame)) ||
3098 (((this_frame->coded_error > (next_frame->coded_error * 1.2)) &&
3099 (this_frame->coded_error > (last_frame->coded_error * 1.2))) &&
3100 (pcnt_intra > MIN_INTRA_LEVEL) &&
3101 ((pcnt_intra + this_frame->pcnt_neutral) > 0.5) &&
3102 ((this_frame->intra_error /
3103 DOUBLE_DIVIDE_CHECK(this_frame->coded_error)) <
3104 KF_II_ERR_THRESHOLD)))) {
3105 int i;
3106 double boost_score = 0.0;
3107 double old_boost_score = 0.0;
3108 double decay_accumulator = 1.0;
3109
3110 // Examine how well the key frame predicts subsequent frames.
3111 for (i = 0; i < 16; ++i) {
3112 const FIRSTPASS_STATS *frame_stats =
3113 fps_get_frame_stats(first_pass_info, show_idx + 1 + i);
3114 double next_iiratio = (II_FACTOR * frame_stats->intra_error /
3115 DOUBLE_DIVIDE_CHECK(frame_stats->coded_error));
3116
3117 if (next_iiratio > KF_II_MAX) next_iiratio = KF_II_MAX;
3118
3119 // Cumulative effect of decay in prediction quality.
3120 if (frame_stats->pcnt_inter > 0.85)
3121 decay_accumulator *= frame_stats->pcnt_inter;
3122 else
3123 decay_accumulator *= (0.85 + frame_stats->pcnt_inter) / 2.0;
3124
3125 // Keep a running total.
3126 boost_score += (decay_accumulator * next_iiratio);
3127
3128 // Test various breakout clauses.
3129 if ((frame_stats->pcnt_inter < 0.05) || (next_iiratio < 1.5) ||
3130 (((frame_stats->pcnt_inter - frame_stats->pcnt_neutral) < 0.20) &&
3131 (next_iiratio < 3.0)) ||
3132 ((boost_score - old_boost_score) < 3.0) ||
3133 (frame_stats->intra_error < V_LOW_INTRA)) {
3134 break;
3135 }
3136
3137 old_boost_score = boost_score;
3138
3139 // Get the next frame details
3140 if (show_idx + 1 + i == fps_get_num_frames(first_pass_info) - 1) break;
3141 }
3142
3143 // If there is tolerable prediction for at least the next 3 frames then
3144 // break out else discard this potential key frame and move on
3145 if (boost_score > 30.0 && (i > 3)) {
3146 is_viable_kf = 1;
3147 } else {
3148 is_viable_kf = 0;
3149 }
3150 }
3151
3152 return is_viable_kf;
3153}
3154
3155#define FRAMES_TO_CHECK_DECAY 8
3156#define MIN_KF_TOT_BOOST 300
3157#define DEFAULT_SCAN_FRAMES_FOR_KF_BOOST 32
3158#define MAX_SCAN_FRAMES_FOR_KF_BOOST 48
3159#define MIN_SCAN_FRAMES_FOR_KF_BOOST 32
3160#define KF_ABS_ZOOM_THRESH 6.0
3161
3162#ifdef AGGRESSIVE_VBR
3163#define KF_MAX_FRAME_BOOST 80.0
3164#define MAX_KF_TOT_BOOST 4800
3165#else
3166#define KF_MAX_FRAME_BOOST 96.0
3167#define MAX_KF_TOT_BOOST 5400
3168#endif
3169
3170int vp9_get_frames_to_next_key(const VP9EncoderConfig *oxcf,
3171 const FRAME_INFO *frame_info,
3172 const FIRST_PASS_INFO *first_pass_info,
3173 int kf_show_idx, int min_gf_interval) {
3174 double recent_loop_decay[FRAMES_TO_CHECK_DECAY];
3175 int j;
3176 int frames_to_key;
3177 int max_frames_to_key = first_pass_info->num_frames - kf_show_idx;
3178 max_frames_to_key = VPXMIN(max_frames_to_key, oxcf->key_freq);
3179
3180 // Initialize the decay rates for the recent frames to check
3181 for (j = 0; j < FRAMES_TO_CHECK_DECAY; ++j) recent_loop_decay[j] = 1.0;
3182 // Find the next keyframe.
3183 if (!oxcf->auto_key) {
3184 frames_to_key = max_frames_to_key;
3185 } else {
3186 frames_to_key = 1;
3187 while (frames_to_key < max_frames_to_key) {
3188 // Provided that we are not at the end of the file...
3189 if (kf_show_idx + frames_to_key + 1 < first_pass_info->num_frames) {
3190 double loop_decay_rate;
3191 double decay_accumulator;
3192 const FIRSTPASS_STATS *next_frame = fps_get_frame_stats(
3193 first_pass_info, kf_show_idx + frames_to_key + 1);
3194
3195 // Check for a scene cut.
3196 if (test_candidate_kf(first_pass_info, kf_show_idx + frames_to_key))
3197 break;
3198
3199 // How fast is the prediction quality decaying?
3200 loop_decay_rate = get_prediction_decay_rate(frame_info, next_frame);
3201
3202 // We want to know something about the recent past... rather than
3203 // as used elsewhere where we are concerned with decay in prediction
3204 // quality since the last GF or KF.
3205 recent_loop_decay[(frames_to_key - 1) % FRAMES_TO_CHECK_DECAY] =
3206 loop_decay_rate;
3207 decay_accumulator = 1.0;
3208 for (j = 0; j < FRAMES_TO_CHECK_DECAY; ++j)
3209 decay_accumulator *= recent_loop_decay[j];
3210
3211 // Special check for transition or high motion followed by a
3212 // static scene.
3213 if ((frames_to_key - 1) > min_gf_interval && loop_decay_rate >= 0.999 &&
3214 decay_accumulator < 0.9) {
3215 int still_interval = oxcf->key_freq - (frames_to_key - 1);
3216 // TODO(angiebird): Figure out why we use "+1" here
3217 int show_idx = kf_show_idx + frames_to_key;
3218 if (check_transition_to_still(first_pass_info, show_idx,
3219 still_interval)) {
3220 break;
3221 }
3222 }
3223 }
3224 ++frames_to_key;
3225 }
3226 }
3227 return frames_to_key;
3228}

3230static void find_next_key_frame(VP9_COMP *cpi, int kf_show_idx) {
3231 int i;
3232 RATE_CONTROL *const rc = &cpi->rc;
3233 TWO_PASS *const twopass = &cpi->twopass;
3234 GF_GROUP *const gf_group = &twopass->gf_group;
3235 const VP9EncoderConfig *const oxcf = &cpi->oxcf;
3236 const FIRST_PASS_INFO *first_pass_info = &twopass->first_pass_info;
3237 const FRAME_INFO *frame_info = &cpi->frame_info;
3238 const FIRSTPASS_STATS *const start_position = twopass->stats_in;
3239 const FIRSTPASS_STATS *keyframe_stats =
3240 fps_get_frame_stats(first_pass_info, kf_show_idx);
3241 FIRSTPASS_STATS next_frame;
3242 int kf_bits = 0;
3243 int64_t max_kf_bits;
3244 double zero_motion_accumulator = 1.0;
3245 double zero_motion_sum = 0.0;
3246 double zero_motion_avg;
3247 double motion_compensable_sum = 0.0;
3248 double motion_compensable_avg;
3249 int num_frames = 0;
3250 int kf_boost_scan_frames = DEFAULT_SCAN_FRAMES_FOR_KF_BOOST;
3251 double boost_score = 0.0;
3252 double kf_mod_err = 0.0;
3253 double kf_raw_err = 0.0;
3254 double kf_group_err = 0.0;
3255 double sr_accumulator = 0.0;
3256 double abs_mv_in_out_accumulator = 0.0;
3257 const double av_err = get_distribution_av_err(cpi, twopass);
3258 const double mean_mod_score = twopass->mean_mod_score;
3259 vp9_zero(next_frame);
3260
3261 cpi->common.frame_type = KEY_FRAME;
3262 rc->frames_since_key = 0;
3263
3264 // Reset the GF group data structures.
3265 vp9_zero(*gf_group);
3266
3267 // Is this a forced key frame by interval.
3268 rc->this_key_frame_forced = rc->next_key_frame_forced;
3269
3270 // Clear the alt ref active flag and last group multi arf flags as they
3271 // can never be set for a key frame.
3272 rc->source_alt_ref_active = 0;
3273
3274 // KF is always a GF so clear frames till next gf counter.
3275 rc->frames_till_gf_update_due = 0;
3276
3277 rc->frames_to_key = 1;
3278
3279 twopass->kf_group_bits = 0; // Total bits available to kf group
3280 twopass->kf_group_error_left = 0.0; // Group modified error score.
3281
3282 kf_raw_err = keyframe_stats->intra_error;
3283 kf_mod_err = calc_norm_frame_score(oxcf, frame_info, keyframe_stats,
3284 mean_mod_score, av_err);
3285
3286 rc->frames_to_key = vp9_get_frames_to_next_key(
3287 oxcf, frame_info, first_pass_info, kf_show_idx, rc->min_gf_interval);
3288
3289 // If there is a max kf interval set by the user we must obey it.
3290 // We already breakout of the loop above at 2x max.
3291 // This code centers the extra kf if the actual natural interval
3292 // is between 1x and 2x.
3293 if (rc->frames_to_key >= cpi->oxcf.key_freq) {
3294 rc->next_key_frame_forced = 1;
3295 } else {
3296 rc->next_key_frame_forced = 0;
3297 }
3298
3299 for (i = 0; i < rc->frames_to_key; ++i) {
3300 const FIRSTPASS_STATS *frame_stats =
3301 fps_get_frame_stats(first_pass_info, kf_show_idx + i);
3302 // Accumulate kf group error.
3303 kf_group_err += calc_norm_frame_score(oxcf, frame_info, frame_stats,
3304 mean_mod_score, av_err);
3305 }
3306
3307 // Calculate the number of bits that should be assigned to the kf group.
3308 if (twopass->bits_left > 0 && twopass->normalized_score_left > 0.0) {
3309 // Maximum number of bits for a single normal frame (not key frame).
3310 const int max_bits = frame_max_bits(rc, &cpi->oxcf);
3311
3312 // Maximum number of bits allocated to the key frame group.
3313 int64_t max_grp_bits;
3314
3315 // Default allocation based on bits left and relative
3316 // complexity of the section.
3317 twopass->kf_group_bits = (int64_t)(
3318 twopass->bits_left * (kf_group_err / twopass->normalized_score_left));
3319
3320 // Clip based on maximum per frame rate defined by the user.
3321 max_grp_bits = (int64_t)max_bits * (int64_t)rc->frames_to_key;
3322 if (twopass->kf_group_bits > max_grp_bits)
3323 twopass->kf_group_bits = max_grp_bits;
3324 } else {
3325 twopass->kf_group_bits = 0;
3326 }
3327 twopass->kf_group_bits = VPXMAX(0, twopass->kf_group_bits);
3328
3329 // Scan through the kf group collating various stats used to determine
3330 // how many bits to spend on it.
3331 boost_score = 0.0;
3332
3333 for (i = 0; i < VPXMIN(MAX_SCAN_FRAMES_FOR_KF_BOOST, (rc->frames_to_key - 1));
3334 ++i) {
3335 if (EOF == input_stats(twopass, &next_frame)) break;
3336
3337 zero_motion_sum += next_frame.pcnt_inter - next_frame.pcnt_motion;
3338 motion_compensable_sum +=
3339 1 - (double)next_frame.coded_error / next_frame.intra_error;
3340 num_frames++;
3341 }
3342
3343 if (num_frames >= MIN_SCAN_FRAMES_FOR_KF_BOOST) {
3344 zero_motion_avg = zero_motion_sum / num_frames;
3345 motion_compensable_avg = motion_compensable_sum / num_frames;
3346 kf_boost_scan_frames = (int)(VPXMAX(64 * zero_motion_avg - 16,
3347 160 * motion_compensable_avg - 112));
3348 kf_boost_scan_frames =
3349 VPXMAX(VPXMIN(kf_boost_scan_frames, MAX_SCAN_FRAMES_FOR_KF_BOOST),
3350 MIN_SCAN_FRAMES_FOR_KF_BOOST);
3351 }
3352 reset_fpf_position(twopass, start_position);
3353
3354 for (i = 0; i < (rc->frames_to_key - 1); ++i) {
3355 if (EOF == input_stats(twopass, &next_frame)) break;
3356
3357 // The zero motion test here insures that if we mark a kf group as static
3358 // it is static throughout not just the first KF_BOOST_SCAN_MAX_FRAMES.
3359 // It also allows for a larger boost on long static groups.
3360 if ((i <= kf_boost_scan_frames) || (zero_motion_accumulator >= 0.99)) {
3361 double frame_boost;
3362 double zm_factor;
3363
3364 // Monitor for static sections.
3365 // First frame in kf group the second ref indicator is invalid.
3366 if (i > 0) {
3367 zero_motion_accumulator =
3368 VPXMIN(zero_motion_accumulator,
3369 get_zero_motion_factor(&cpi->frame_info, &next_frame));
3370 } else {
3371 zero_motion_accumulator =
3372 next_frame.pcnt_inter - next_frame.pcnt_motion;
3373 }
3374
3375 // Factor 0.75-1.25 based on how much of frame is static.
3376 zm_factor = (0.75 + (zero_motion_accumulator / 2.0));
3377
3378 // The second (lagging) ref error is not valid immediately after
3379 // a key frame because either the lag has not built up (in the case of
3380 // the first key frame or it points to a refernce before the new key
3381 // frame.
3382 if (i < 2) sr_accumulator = 0.0;
3383 frame_boost = calc_kf_frame_boost(cpi, &next_frame, &sr_accumulator, 0,
3384 KF_MAX_FRAME_BOOST * zm_factor);
3385
3386 boost_score += frame_boost;
3387
3388 // Measure of zoom. Large zoom tends to indicate reduced boost.
3389 abs_mv_in_out_accumulator +=
3390 fabs(next_frame.mv_in_out_count * next_frame.pcnt_motion);
3391
3392 if ((frame_boost < 25.00) ||
3393 (abs_mv_in_out_accumulator > KF_ABS_ZOOM_THRESH) ||
3394 (sr_accumulator > (kf_raw_err * 1.50)))
3395 break;
3396 } else {
3397 break;
3398 }
3399 }
3400
3401 reset_fpf_position(twopass, start_position);
3402
3403 // Store the zero motion percentage
3404 twopass->kf_zeromotion_pct = (int)(zero_motion_accumulator * 100.0);
3405
3406 // Calculate a section intra ratio used in setting max loop filter.
3407 twopass->key_frame_section_intra_rating = calculate_section_intra_ratio(
3408 start_position, twopass->stats_in_end, rc->frames_to_key);
3409
3410 // Special case for static / slide show content but dont apply
3411 // if the kf group is very short.
3412 if ((zero_motion_accumulator > 0.99) && (rc->frames_to_key > 8)) {
3413 rc->kf_boost = MAX_KF_TOT_BOOST;
3414 } else {
3415 // Apply various clamps for min and max boost
3416 rc->kf_boost = VPXMAX((int)boost_score, (rc->frames_to_key * 3));
3417 rc->kf_boost = VPXMAX(rc->kf_boost, MIN_KF_TOT_BOOST);
3418 rc->kf_boost = VPXMIN(rc->kf_boost, MAX_KF_TOT_BOOST);
3419 }
3420
3421 // Work out how many bits to allocate for the key frame itself.
3422 kf_bits = calculate_boost_bits((rc->frames_to_key - 1), rc->kf_boost,
3423 twopass->kf_group_bits);
3424 // Based on the spatial complexity, increase the bits allocated to key frame.
3425 kf_bits +=
3426 (int)((twopass->kf_group_bits - kf_bits) * (kf_mod_err / kf_group_err));
3427 max_kf_bits =
3428 twopass->kf_group_bits - (rc->frames_to_key - 1) * FRAME_OVERHEAD_BITS;
3429 max_kf_bits = lclamp(max_kf_bits, 0, INT_MAX);
3430 kf_bits = VPXMIN(kf_bits, (int)max_kf_bits);
3431
3432 twopass->kf_group_bits -= kf_bits;
3433
3434 // Save the bits to spend on the key frame.
3435 gf_group->bit_allocation[0] = kf_bits;
3436 gf_group->update_type[0] = KF_UPDATE;
3437 gf_group->rf_level[0] = KF_STD;
3438 gf_group->layer_depth[0] = 0;
3439
3440 // Note the total error score of the kf group minus the key frame itself.
3441 twopass->kf_group_error_left = (kf_group_err - kf_mod_err);
3442
3443 // Adjust the count of total modified error left.
3444 // The count of bits left is adjusted elsewhere based on real coded frame
3445 // sizes.
3446 twopass->normalized_score_left -= kf_group_err;
3447
3448 if (oxcf->resize_mode == RESIZE_DYNAMIC) {
3449 // Default to normal-sized frame on keyframes.
3450 cpi->rc.next_frame_size_selector = UNSCALED;
3451 }
3452}
3453
3454static int is_skippable_frame(const VP9_COMP *cpi) {
3455 // If the current frame does not have non-zero motion vector detected in the
3456 // first pass, and so do its previous and forward frames, then this frame
3457 // can be skipped for partition check, and the partition size is assigned
3458 // according to the variance
3459 const TWO_PASS *const twopass = &cpi->twopass;
3460
3461 return (!frame_is_intra_only(&cpi->common) &&
3462 twopass->stats_in - 2 > twopass->stats_in_start &&
3463 twopass->stats_in < twopass->stats_in_end &&
3464 (twopass->stats_in - 1)->pcnt_inter -
3465 (twopass->stats_in - 1)->pcnt_motion ==
3466 1 &&
3467 (twopass->stats_in - 2)->pcnt_inter -
3468 (twopass->stats_in - 2)->pcnt_motion ==
3469 1 &&
3470 twopass->stats_in->pcnt_inter - twopass->stats_in->pcnt_motion == 1);
3471}

3473void vp9_rc_get_second_pass_params(VP9_COMP *cpi) {
3474 VP9_COMMON *const cm = &cpi->common;
3475 RATE_CONTROL *const rc = &cpi->rc;
3476 TWO_PASS *const twopass = &cpi->twopass;
3477 GF_GROUP *const gf_group = &twopass->gf_group;
3478 FIRSTPASS_STATS this_frame;
3479 const int show_idx = cm->current_video_frame;
3480
3481 if (!twopass->stats_in) return;
3482
3483 // If this is an arf frame then we dont want to read the stats file or
3484 // advance the input pointer as we already have what we need.
3485 if (gf_group->update_type[gf_group->index] == ARF_UPDATE) {
3486 int target_rate;
3487
3488 vp9_zero(this_frame);
3489 this_frame =
3490 cpi->twopass.stats_in_start[cm->current_video_frame +
3491 gf_group->arf_src_offset[gf_group->index]];
3492
3493 vp9_configure_buffer_updates(cpi, gf_group->index);
3494
3495 target_rate = gf_group->bit_allocation[gf_group->index];
3496 target_rate = vp9_rc_clamp_pframe_target_size(cpi, target_rate);
3497 rc->base_frame_target = target_rate;
3498
3499 cm->frame_type = INTER_FRAME;
3500
3501 // Do the firstpass stats indicate that this frame is skippable for the
3502 // partition search?
3503 if (cpi->sf.allow_partition_search_skip && cpi->oxcf.pass == 2 &&
3504 !cpi->use_svc) {
3505 cpi->partition_search_skippable_frame = is_skippable_frame(cpi);
3506 }
3507
3508 // The multiplication by 256 reverses a scaling factor of (>> 8)
3509 // applied when combining MB error values for the frame.
3510 twopass->mb_av_energy = log((this_frame.intra_error * 256.0) + 1.0);
3511 twopass->mb_smooth_pct = this_frame.intra_smooth_pct;
3512
3513 return;
3514 }
3515
3516 vpx_clear_system_state();
3517
3518 if (cpi->oxcf.rc_mode == VPX_Q) {
3519 twopass->active_worst_quality = cpi->oxcf.cq_level;
3520 } else if (cm->current_video_frame == 0) {
3521 const int frames_left =
3522 (int)(twopass->total_stats.count - cm->current_video_frame);
3523 // Special case code for first frame.
3524 const int section_target_bandwidth =
3525 (int)(twopass->bits_left / frames_left);
3526 const double section_length = twopass->total_left_stats.count;
3527 const double section_error =
3528 twopass->total_left_stats.coded_error / section_length;
3529 const double section_intra_skip =
3530 twopass->total_left_stats.intra_skip_pct / section_length;
3531 const double section_inactive_zone =
3532 (twopass->total_left_stats.inactive_zone_rows * 2) /
3533 ((double)cm->mb_rows * section_length);
3534 const double section_noise =
3535 twopass->total_left_stats.frame_noise_energy / section_length;
3536 int tmp_q;
3537
3538 tmp_q = get_twopass_worst_quality(
3539 cpi, section_error, section_intra_skip + section_inactive_zone,
3540 section_noise, section_target_bandwidth);
3541
3542 twopass->active_worst_quality = tmp_q;
3543 twopass->baseline_active_worst_quality = tmp_q;
3544 rc->ni_av_qi = tmp_q;
3545 rc->last_q[INTER_FRAME] = tmp_q;
3546 rc->avg_q = vp9_convert_qindex_to_q(tmp_q, cm->bit_depth);
3547 rc->avg_frame_qindex[INTER_FRAME] = tmp_q;
3548 rc->last_q[KEY_FRAME] = (tmp_q + cpi->oxcf.best_allowed_q) / 2;
3549 rc->avg_frame_qindex[KEY_FRAME] = rc->last_q[KEY_FRAME];
3550 }
3551 vp9_zero(this_frame);
3552 if (EOF == input_stats(twopass, &this_frame)) return;
3553
3554 // Set the frame content type flag.
3555 if (this_frame.intra_skip_pct >= FC_ANIMATION_THRESH)
3556 twopass->fr_content_type = FC_GRAPHICS_ANIMATION;
3557 else
3558 twopass->fr_content_type = FC_NORMAL;
3559
3560 // Keyframe and section processing.
3561 if (rc->frames_to_key == 0 || (cpi->frame_flags & FRAMEFLAGS_KEY)) {
3562 // Define next KF group and assign bits to it.
3563 find_next_key_frame(cpi, show_idx);
3564 } else {
3565 cm->frame_type = INTER_FRAME;
3566 }
3567
3568 // Define a new GF/ARF group. (Should always enter here for key frames).
3569 if (rc->frames_till_gf_update_due == 0) {
3570 define_gf_group(cpi, show_idx);
3571
3572 rc->frames_till_gf_update_due = rc->baseline_gf_interval;
3573
3574#if ARF_STATS_OUTPUT
3575 {
3576 FILE *fpfile;
3577 fpfile = fopen("arf.stt", "a");
3578 ++arf_count;
3579 fprintf(fpfile, "%10d %10ld %10d %10d %10ld %10ld\n",
3580 cm->current_video_frame, rc->frames_till_gf_update_due,
3581 rc->kf_boost, arf_count, rc->gfu_boost, cm->frame_type);
3582
3583 fclose(fpfile);
3584 }
3585#endif
3586 }
3587
3588 vp9_configure_buffer_updates(cpi, gf_group->index);
3589
3590 // Do the firstpass stats indicate that this frame is skippable for the
3591 // partition search?
3592 if (cpi->sf.allow_partition_search_skip && cpi->oxcf.pass == 2 &&
3593 !cpi->use_svc) {
3594 cpi->partition_search_skippable_frame = is_skippable_frame(cpi);
3595 }
3596
3597 rc->base_frame_target = gf_group->bit_allocation[gf_group->index];
3598
3599 // The multiplication by 256 reverses a scaling factor of (>> 8)
3600 // applied when combining MB error values for the frame.
3601 twopass->mb_av_energy = log((this_frame.intra_error * 256.0) + 1.0);
3602 twopass->mb_smooth_pct = this_frame.intra_smooth_pct;
3603
3604 // Update the total stats remaining structure.
3605 subtract_stats(&twopass->total_left_stats, &this_frame);
3606}

3608#define MINQ_ADJ_LIMIT 48
3609#define MINQ_ADJ_LIMIT_CQ 20
3610#define HIGH_UNDERSHOOT_RATIO 2
3611void vp9_twopass_postencode_update(VP9_COMP *cpi) {
3612 TWO_PASS *const twopass = &cpi->twopass;
3613 RATE_CONTROL *const rc = &cpi->rc;
3614 VP9_COMMON *const cm = &cpi->common;
3615 const int bits_used = rc->base_frame_target;
3616
3617 // VBR correction is done through rc->vbr_bits_off_target. Based on the
3618 // sign of this value, a limited % adjustment is made to the target rate
3619 // of subsequent frames, to try and push it back towards 0. This method
3620 // is designed to prevent extreme behaviour at the end of a clip
3621 // or group of frames.
3622 rc->vbr_bits_off_target += rc->base_frame_target - rc->projected_frame_size;
3623 twopass->bits_left = VPXMAX(twopass->bits_left - bits_used, 0);
3624
3625 // Target vs actual bits for this arf group.
3626 twopass->rolling_arf_group_target_bits += rc->this_frame_target;
3627 twopass->rolling_arf_group_actual_bits += rc->projected_frame_size;
3628
3629 // Calculate the pct rc error.
3630 if (rc->total_actual_bits) {
3631 rc->rate_error_estimate =
3632 (int)((rc->vbr_bits_off_target * 100) / rc->total_actual_bits);
3633 rc->rate_error_estimate = clamp(rc->rate_error_estimate, -100, 100);
3634 } else {
3635 rc->rate_error_estimate = 0;
3636 }
3637
3638 if (cpi->common.frame_type != KEY_FRAME) {
3639 twopass->kf_group_bits -= bits_used;
3640 twopass->last_kfgroup_zeromotion_pct = twopass->kf_zeromotion_pct;
3641 }
3642 twopass->kf_group_bits = VPXMAX(twopass->kf_group_bits, 0);
3643
3644 // Increment the gf group index ready for the next frame.
3645 ++twopass->gf_group.index;
3646
3647 // If the rate control is drifting consider adjustment to min or maxq.
3648 if ((cpi->oxcf.rc_mode != VPX_Q) && !cpi->rc.is_src_frame_alt_ref) {
3649 const int maxq_adj_limit =
3650 rc->worst_quality - twopass->active_worst_quality;
3651 const int minq_adj_limit =
3652 (cpi->oxcf.rc_mode == VPX_CQ ? MINQ_ADJ_LIMIT_CQ : MINQ_ADJ_LIMIT);
3653 int aq_extend_min = 0;
3654 int aq_extend_max = 0;
3655
3656 // Extend min or Max Q range to account for imbalance from the base
3657 // value when using AQ.
3658 if (cpi->oxcf.aq_mode != NO_AQ && cpi->oxcf.aq_mode != PSNR_AQ &&
3659 cpi->oxcf.aq_mode != PERCEPTUAL_AQ) {
3660 if (cm->seg.aq_av_offset < 0) {
3661 // The balance of the AQ map tends towarda lowering the average Q.
3662 aq_extend_min = 0;
3663 aq_extend_max = VPXMIN(maxq_adj_limit, -cm->seg.aq_av_offset);
3664 } else {
3665 // The balance of the AQ map tends towards raising the average Q.
3666 aq_extend_min = VPXMIN(minq_adj_limit, cm->seg.aq_av_offset);
3667 aq_extend_max = 0;
3668 }
3669 }
3670
3671 // Undershoot.
3672 if (rc->rate_error_estimate > cpi->oxcf.under_shoot_pct) {
3673 --twopass->extend_maxq;
3674 if (rc->rolling_target_bits >= rc->rolling_actual_bits)
3675 ++twopass->extend_minq;
3676 // Overshoot.
3677 } else if (rc->rate_error_estimate < -cpi->oxcf.over_shoot_pct) {
3678 --twopass->extend_minq;
3679 if (rc->rolling_target_bits < rc->rolling_actual_bits)
3680 ++twopass->extend_maxq;
3681 } else {
3682 // Adjustment for extreme local overshoot.
3683 if (rc->projected_frame_size > (2 * rc->base_frame_target) &&
3684 rc->projected_frame_size > (2 * rc->avg_frame_bandwidth))
3685 ++twopass->extend_maxq;
3686
3687 // Unwind undershoot or overshoot adjustment.
3688 if (rc->rolling_target_bits < rc->rolling_actual_bits)
3689 --twopass->extend_minq;
3690 else if (rc->rolling_target_bits > rc->rolling_actual_bits)
3691 --twopass->extend_maxq;
3692 }
3693
3694 twopass->extend_minq =
3695 clamp(twopass->extend_minq, aq_extend_min, minq_adj_limit);
3696 twopass->extend_maxq =
3697 clamp(twopass->extend_maxq, aq_extend_max, maxq_adj_limit);
3698
3699 // If there is a big and undexpected undershoot then feed the extra
3700 // bits back in quickly. One situation where this may happen is if a
3701 // frame is unexpectedly almost perfectly predicted by the ARF or GF
3702 // but not very well predcited by the previous frame.
3703 if (!frame_is_kf_gf_arf(cpi) && !cpi->rc.is_src_frame_alt_ref) {
3704 int fast_extra_thresh = rc->base_frame_target / HIGH_UNDERSHOOT_RATIO;
3705 if (rc->projected_frame_size < fast_extra_thresh) {
3706 rc->vbr_bits_off_target_fast +=
3707 fast_extra_thresh - rc->projected_frame_size;
3708 rc->vbr_bits_off_target_fast =
3709 VPXMIN(rc->vbr_bits_off_target_fast, (4 * rc->avg_frame_bandwidth));
3710
3711 // Fast adaptation of minQ if necessary to use up the extra bits.
3712 if (rc->avg_frame_bandwidth) {
3713 twopass->extend_minq_fast =
3714 (int)(rc->vbr_bits_off_target_fast * 8 / rc->avg_frame_bandwidth);
3715 }
3716 twopass->extend_minq_fast = VPXMIN(
3717 twopass->extend_minq_fast, minq_adj_limit - twopass->extend_minq);
3718 } else if (rc->vbr_bits_off_target_fast) {
3719 twopass->extend_minq_fast = VPXMIN(
3720 twopass->extend_minq_fast, minq_adj_limit - twopass->extend_minq);
3721 } else {
3722 twopass->extend_minq_fast = 0;
3723 }
3724 }
3725 }
3726}

3729void vp9_get_next_group_of_picture(const VP9_COMP *cpi, int *first_is_key_frame,
3730 int *use_alt_ref, int *coding_frame_count,
3731 int *first_show_idx,
3732 int *last_gop_use_alt_ref) {
3733 const GOP_COMMAND *gop_command = &cpi->encode_command.gop_command;
3734 // We make a copy of rc here because we want to get information from the
3735 // encoder without changing its state.
3736 // TODO(angiebird): Avoid copying rc here.
3737 RATE_CONTROL rc = cpi->rc;
3738 const int multi_layer_arf = 0;
3739 const int allow_alt_ref = 1;
3740 // We assume that current_video_frame is updated to the show index of the
3741 // frame we are about to called. Note that current_video_frame is updated at
3742 // the end of encode_frame_to_data_rate().
3743 // TODO(angiebird): Avoid this kind of fragile style.
3744 *first_show_idx = cpi->common.current_video_frame;
3745 *last_gop_use_alt_ref = rc.source_alt_ref_active;
3746
3747 *first_is_key_frame = 0;
3748 if (rc.frames_to_key == 0) {
3749 rc.frames_to_key = vp9_get_frames_to_next_key(
3750 &cpi->oxcf, &cpi->frame_info, &cpi->twopass.first_pass_info,
3751 *first_show_idx, rc.min_gf_interval);
3752 rc.frames_since_key = 0;
3753 *first_is_key_frame = 1;
3754 }
3755
3756 if (gop_command->use) {
3757 *coding_frame_count = gop_command_coding_frame_count(gop_command);
3758 *use_alt_ref = gop_command->use_alt_ref;
3759 assert(*coding_frame_count < rc.frames_to_key);
3760 } else {
3761 *coding_frame_count = vp9_get_gop_coding_frame_count(
3762 &cpi->oxcf, &cpi->frame_info, &cpi->twopass.first_pass_info, &rc,
3763 *first_show_idx, multi_layer_arf, allow_alt_ref, *first_is_key_frame,
3764 *last_gop_use_alt_ref, use_alt_ref);
3765 }
3766}

3768int vp9_get_gop_coding_frame_count(const VP9EncoderConfig *oxcf,
3769 const FRAME_INFO *frame_info,
3770 const FIRST_PASS_INFO *first_pass_info,
3771 const RATE_CONTROL *rc, int show_idx,
3772 int multi_layer_arf, int allow_alt_ref,
3773 int first_is_key_frame,
3774 int last_gop_use_alt_ref, int *use_alt_ref) {
3775 int frame_count;
3776 double gop_intra_factor;
3777 const int arf_active_or_kf = last_gop_use_alt_ref || first_is_key_frame;
3778 RANGE active_gf_interval = get_active_gf_inverval_range(
3779 frame_info, rc, arf_active_or_kf, show_idx, /*active_worst_quality=*/0,
3780 /*last_boosted_qindex=*/0);
3781
3782 const int arf_layers = get_arf_layers(multi_layer_arf, oxcf->enable_auto_arf,
3783 active_gf_interval.max);
3784 if (multi_layer_arf) {
3785 gop_intra_factor = 1.0 + 0.25 * arf_layers;
3786 } else {
3787 gop_intra_factor = 1.0;
3788 }
3789
3790 frame_count = get_gop_coding_frame_num(
3791 use_alt_ref, frame_info, first_pass_info, rc, show_idx,
3792 &active_gf_interval, gop_intra_factor, oxcf->lag_in_frames);
3793 *use_alt_ref &= allow_alt_ref;
3794 return frame_count;
3795}

3797// Under CONFIG_RATE_CTRL, once the first_pass_info is ready, the number of
3798// coding frames (including show frame and alt ref) can be determined.
3799int vp9_get_coding_frame_num(const VP9EncoderConfig *oxcf,
3800 const FRAME_INFO *frame_info,
3801 const FIRST_PASS_INFO *first_pass_info,
3802 int multi_layer_arf, int allow_alt_ref) {
3803 int coding_frame_num = 0;
3804 RATE_CONTROL rc;
3805 int gop_coding_frame_count;
3806 int gop_show_frames;
3807 int show_idx = 0;
3808 int last_gop_use_alt_ref = 0;
3809 vp9_rc_init(oxcf, 1, &rc);
3810
3811 while (show_idx < first_pass_info->num_frames) {
3812 int use_alt_ref;
3813 int first_is_key_frame = 0;
3814 if (rc.frames_to_key == 0) {
3815 rc.frames_to_key = vp9_get_frames_to_next_key(
3816 oxcf, frame_info, first_pass_info, show_idx, rc.min_gf_interval);
3817 rc.frames_since_key = 0;
3818 first_is_key_frame = 1;
3819 }
3820
3821 gop_coding_frame_count = vp9_get_gop_coding_frame_count(
3822 oxcf, frame_info, first_pass_info, &rc, show_idx, multi_layer_arf,
3823 allow_alt_ref, first_is_key_frame, last_gop_use_alt_ref, &use_alt_ref);
3824
3825 rc.source_alt_ref_active = use_alt_ref;
3826 last_gop_use_alt_ref = use_alt_ref;
3827 gop_show_frames = gop_coding_frame_count - use_alt_ref;
3828 rc.frames_to_key -= gop_show_frames;
3829 rc.frames_since_key += gop_show_frames;
3830 show_idx += gop_show_frames;
3831 coding_frame_num += gop_show_frames + use_alt_ref;
3832 }
3833 return coding_frame_num;
3834}

3836void vp9_get_key_frame_map(const VP9EncoderConfig *oxcf,
3837 const FRAME_INFO *frame_info,
3838 const FIRST_PASS_INFO *first_pass_info,
3839 int *key_frame_map) {
3840 int show_idx = 0;
3841 RATE_CONTROL rc;
3842 vp9_rc_init(oxcf, 1, &rc);
3843
3844 // key_frame_map points to an int array with size equal to
3845 // first_pass_info->num_frames, which is also the number of show frames in the
3846 // video.
3847 memset(key_frame_map, 0,
3848 sizeof(*key_frame_map) * first_pass_info->num_frames);
3849 while (show_idx < first_pass_info->num_frames) {
3850 int key_frame_group_size;
3851 key_frame_map[show_idx] = 1;
3852 key_frame_group_size = vp9_get_frames_to_next_key(
3853 oxcf, frame_info, first_pass_info, show_idx, rc.min_gf_interval);
3854 assert(key_frame_group_size > 0);
3855 show_idx += key_frame_group_size;
3856 }
3857 assert(show_idx == first_pass_info->num_frames);
3858}
